1
00:00:00,080 --> 00:00:04,880
A HARUKI KADOKAWA OFFICE
& KITTY FILM CO-PRODUCTION

2
00:00:12,970 --> 00:00:14,010
Oh, God...

3
00:00:14,140 --> 00:00:15,350
Come on, step on it!

4
00:00:15,890 --> 00:00:17,220
I can't go any faster!

5
00:00:17,350 --> 00:00:19,430
Bullshit! Speed up or you're dead!

6
00:00:19,890 --> 00:00:21,060
This is as fast as it goes!

7
00:00:21,180 --> 00:00:23,440
This is? You're only doing 60.

8
00:00:23,560 --> 00:00:25,520
Your speedometer goes up to 160.

9
00:00:27,150 --> 00:00:29,230
That's the radio, brainiac!

10
00:00:30,280 --> 00:00:31,400
Radio?

11
00:00:31,990 --> 00:00:33,240
I'm shortsighted, you see.

12
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:37,330
Anyway, never mind that! Just hurry up!
That way! Towards the bridge!

13
00:00:37,450 --> 00:00:39,120
- Right?
- Yes! Turn here!

14
00:00:39,240 --> 00:00:40,750
Right! Come on, turn!

15
00:00:40,870 --> 00:00:43,040
What are you doing?

16
00:00:43,540 --> 00:00:46,630
Get moving! Now! You're so damn slow!

17
00:00:46,750 --> 00:00:48,000
- How big's your family?
- Huh?

18
00:00:48,130 --> 00:00:49,210
- How many people?
- Eight.

19
00:00:49,340 --> 00:00:51,550
Eight? They can do without you, then.

20
00:00:51,670 --> 00:00:52,970
Come on, hurry up.

21
00:00:53,090 --> 00:00:55,890
I said, hurry up! That's it, through here.

22
00:01:00,180 --> 00:01:01,850
Brother!

23
00:01:01,980 --> 00:01:04,020
- Now you say it, too.
- Brother!

24
00:01:04,140 --> 00:01:06,440
That's it, very good.
Maybe you can join us.

25
00:01:06,560 --> 00:01:08,650
Alright, stop. Stop, I said!

26
00:01:09,270 --> 00:01:10,610
That's him, over there.

27
00:01:10,730 --> 00:01:12,030
Alright, here we are!

28
00:01:12,150 --> 00:01:13,610
Don't forget your bag!

29
00:01:17,280 --> 00:01:20,540
It might be best to notify his family.

30
00:01:21,700 --> 00:01:24,210
Though they likely
won't get here in time...

31
00:01:24,330 --> 00:01:25,790
He has no family.

32
00:01:28,250 --> 00:01:29,380
Any relatives?

33
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:32,260
Can't you save him?

34
00:01:32,380 --> 00:01:33,630
Aren't you a doctor?!

35
00:01:34,090 --> 00:01:38,340
All I can really do is reduce his pain...

36
00:01:38,470 --> 00:01:39,510
Then do that.

37
00:01:41,470 --> 00:01:42,720
Of course.

38
00:01:50,060 --> 00:01:51,320
Hold on a second.

39
00:01:52,230 --> 00:01:54,490
That needle's ridiculous!

40
00:01:54,610 --> 00:01:56,110
I don't have any for humans.

41
00:01:56,650 --> 00:01:57,820
- I'm a vet.
- Wha?

42
00:01:58,820 --> 00:02:00,070
Sorry!

43
00:02:00,200 --> 00:02:01,240
Hospital!

44
00:02:01,990 --> 00:02:03,450
It said "hospital" on the sign!

45
00:02:03,580 --> 00:02:05,620
Yes, "animal hospital"...

46
00:02:06,500 --> 00:02:07,830
Moron!

47
00:02:07,960 --> 00:02:09,500
- Sakuma.
- Yes, boss?

48
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,340
- Masa.
- Boss!

49
00:02:12,920 --> 00:02:14,800
- Mei.
- Yes?

50
00:02:14,920 --> 00:02:16,130
- Hiko.
- Yes!

51
00:02:22,850 --> 00:02:27,850
I need to talk to you about my successor
as head of the Medaka Family.

52
00:02:27,980 --> 00:02:29,020
Yes, boss?

53
00:02:29,770 --> 00:02:32,820
Let my nephew take over.

54
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:35,030
Where is he?

55
00:02:36,490 --> 00:02:38,700
His name is...

56
00:02:42,280 --> 00:02:47,290
<i>These aren't tears.</i>

57
00:02:48,460 --> 00:02:52,630
<i>ALL this is.</i>

58
00:02:54,090 --> 00:02:59,090
<i>Is where the fickle rain.</i>

59
00:03:00,340 --> 00:03:04,470
<i>Has wet my cheeks a little.</i>

60
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:11,980
<i>This is Algeria, at the end of the earth.</i>

61
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:18,740
<i>And in the casbah night.</i>

62
00:03:20,320 --> 00:03:23,280
<i>The flower will bloom regardless.</i>

63
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,200
Izumi!

64
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:27,580
- Izumi!
- Izumi!

65
00:03:29,370 --> 00:03:31,670
What are you doing here?
Don't you have class?

66
00:03:32,130 --> 00:03:35,210
Who cares about class?
It's your dad's funeral.

67
00:03:35,340 --> 00:03:37,090
We wanted to pay our respects.

68
00:03:37,590 --> 00:03:40,090
- Thank you.
- Huh? Is it just you here?

69
00:03:41,970 --> 00:03:43,550
I don't have a single relative.

70
00:03:44,010 --> 00:03:45,180
And now I'm an orphan!

71
00:03:45,300 --> 00:03:48,810
What about your dad's
friends and colleagues?

72
00:03:49,890 --> 00:03:51,810
I didn't tell anyone.

73
00:03:51,940 --> 00:03:54,650
I wanted to see him off to heaven
by myself.

74
00:03:54,770 --> 00:03:56,070
You really loved him, huh?

75
00:03:56,190 --> 00:04:00,990
Well, to tell you the truth,
ever since Mom died,

76
00:04:01,110 --> 00:04:06,280
I was like his daughter, wife,
and mother, all rolled into one.

77
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:10,370
So I wanted to take good care of him,
right until the very end.

78
00:04:54,330 --> 00:04:56,580
Please place your hands together
in prayer.

79
00:05:21,070 --> 00:05:28,070
SAILOR SUIT AND MACHINE GUN

80
00:05:35,370 --> 00:05:37,040
Cheer up!

81
00:05:39,960 --> 00:05:41,300
Hang in there, okay?

82
00:05:43,670 --> 00:05:45,220
HIROKO YAKUSHIMARU

83
00:05:45,340 --> 00:05:46,680
Come back to school soon.

84
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:51,560
YUKI KAZAMATSURI MASAAKI DAIMON

85
00:05:51,680 --> 00:05:55,560
SHINGO YANAGISAWA
SHINPEI HAYASHIYA

86
00:05:55,690 --> 00:05:57,520
MINORI TERADA TOSHIYA SAKAI

87
00:05:57,650 --> 00:06:01,020
Thanks! You guys should go
back to school now.

88
00:06:01,150 --> 00:06:02,900
- See you later.
- Bye!

89
