97
00:06:46,820 --> 00:06:48,400
I'm all alone now.

98
00:06:50,360 --> 00:06:51,910
But

99
00:06:52,910 --> 00:06:54,410
I'll be okay.

100
00:07:06,170 --> 00:07:07,340
Who are you?

101
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:10,340
Are you Izumi?

102
00:07:11,050 --> 00:07:13,430
Yes, Izumi Hoshi. Why?

103
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:16,600
My name is Mayumi. Nice to meet you.

104
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:20,650
Can I help you?

105
00:07:23,690 --> 00:07:25,520
Can we go inside?

106
00:07:26,070 --> 00:07:28,280
My father said I'm not to let strangers in.

107
00:07:29,700 --> 00:07:31,360
I'm not a stranger.

108
00:07:33,660 --> 00:07:36,200
Takashi talked about you all the time.

109
00:07:39,120 --> 00:07:40,580
Takashi?

110
00:07:41,210 --> 00:07:44,000
Takashi Hoshi. Your dad.

111
00:08:05,940 --> 00:08:07,190
Nice place.

112
00:08:15,990 --> 00:08:17,240
Don't touch that!

113
00:08:22,460 --> 00:08:24,080
I don't want a stranger touching that.

114
00:08:33,800 --> 00:08:34,840
Here.

115
00:08:36,720 --> 00:08:37,760
What is it?

116
00:08:38,310 --> 00:08:39,600
I'd like you to read it.

117
00:08:50,480 --> 00:08:51,860
My dad wrote this?

118
00:08:58,450 --> 00:09:03,500
"Dear Mayumi, since I have to travel
overseas with my company,"

119
00:09:03,620 --> 00:09:07,000
"there's always a risk
I'll have some kind of accident."

120
00:09:07,130 --> 00:09:11,420
"Should the worst happen, I ask that you
go and live with my daughter, Izumi."

121
00:09:11,550 --> 00:09:15,760
"Izumi is a strong, sensible girl,"

122
00:09:15,890 --> 00:09:18,720
"but she's also very naive."

123
00:09:18,850 --> 00:09:24,600
"Getting to know you will open up
her outlook on life,"

124
00:09:24,730 --> 00:09:29,520
"which is what she needs.
Please take good care of her."

125
00:09:29,650 --> 00:09:35,200
"May you also be blessed
with happiness."

126
00:09:35,320 --> 00:09:38,780
"Forever yours, Takashi."

127
00:09:42,750 --> 00:09:43,910
Excuse me,

128
00:09:45,620 --> 00:09:47,880
but what was your relationship
with my father?

129
00:09:56,590 --> 00:09:58,090
Was it

130
00:10:01,350 --> 00:10:05,390
you know, like a man-and-woman thing?

131
00:10:12,690 --> 00:10:14,030
To put it bluntly

132
00:10:18,410 --> 00:10:19,740
are you

133
00:10:22,330 --> 00:10:23,540
my father's mistress?

134
00:10:49,310 --> 00:10:50,650
This blows!

135
00:10:52,520 --> 00:10:53,690
- Tomoo!
- Yes, sir?

136
00:10:53,820 --> 00:10:55,530
Leave quietly if you don't want to paint.

137
00:10:56,030 --> 00:10:57,070
Sorry, sir.

138
00:11:00,110 --> 00:11:01,950
Shouldn't the nose be a bit bigger?

139
00:11:06,080 --> 00:11:07,710
That looks nothing like her!

140
00:11:09,170 --> 00:11:12,590
You're right, it does
look nothing like her.

141
00:11:13,130 --> 00:11:15,090
Alright, that's enough for me.
I'm going home.

142
00:11:17,300 --> 00:11:19,510
Hey, Izumi! Look!

143
00:11:23,260 --> 00:11:24,930
- Who are they?
- What are they doing?

144
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:35,190
It's dangerous here!
What if one of them shoots at us?

145
00:11:36,230 --> 00:11:38,190
Everyone, get back!

146
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:41,160
Can't you hear me?

147
00:11:42,240 --> 00:11:43,490
- Out of the way!
- Stay back!

148
00:11:47,240 --> 00:11:49,540
What do they want?

149
00:11:50,660 --> 00:11:52,420
Nobody knows! That's the weird thing.

150
00:11:52,540 --> 00:11:54,460
Let's go! We're late already.

151
00:11:54,590 --> 00:11:56,590
Alright! We'll escort Izumi home.

152
00:11:56,710 --> 00:11:58,170
Through the back gate?

153
00:11:58,300 --> 00:12:00,010
What else can we do?

154
00:12:00,130 --> 00:12:01,380
I don't want to go that way!

155
00:12:01,510 --> 00:12:02,680
What way do you want to go?

156
00:12:03,220 --> 00:12:04,350
That way.

157
00:12:04,470 --> 00:12:05,850
That way?

158
00:12:06,140 --> 00:12:07,310
It's too dangerous!

159
00:12:07,890 --> 00:12:10,310
This is our school, isn't it?

160
00:12:11,100 --> 00:12:14,150
Why should we have to sneak
out the back?

161
00:12:14,770 --> 00:12:15,900
Hey, Izumi!

162
00:12:16,020 --> 00:12:17,980
- Wait up!
- Stop right there!

163
00:12:18,110 --> 00:12:19,190
Get back here!

164
00:12:20,610 --> 00:12:22,240
Turn around this instant!

165
00:12:23,200 --> 00:12:24,620
Izumi Hoshi!

166
00:12:24,740 --> 00:12:27,990
Come back here!
Leave through the back gate!

167
00:12:31,660 --> 00:12:32,960
Listen to your teachers!

168
00:13:10,410 --> 00:13:12,830
Izumi Hoshi.

169
00:13:14,250 --> 00:13:15,370
Correct?

170
00:13:18,540 --> 00:13:19,750
We're here to pick you up.

171
00:13:26,930 --> 00:13:28,140
Go on.

172
00:14:24,400 --> 00:14:25,440
Excuse me.

173
00:14:31,370 --> 00:14:32,410
Go on up.

174
00:14:33,290 --> 00:14:34,330
Go on!

175
00:14:57,640 --> 00:14:59,020
The Medaka Family?

176
00:15:00,350 --> 00:15:02,020
Is that the yakuza or something?

177
00:15:02,150 --> 00:15:03,940
The Medaka Family has
an honorable history

178
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:06,030
that goes back to the days
before the war.

179
00:15:07,400 --> 00:15:09,740
Don't think we're like the scum
you see these days.

180
00:15:16,080 --> 00:15:17,540
"Fourth Chairman:."

181
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:21,540
"Izumi Hoshi."

182
00:15:25,380 --> 00:15:27,170
Um...

183
00:15:28,420 --> 00:15:31,180
That's the same as my name.

184
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:33,260
It's you.

185
00:15:34,930 --> 00:15:36,470
Allow me to explain.

186
00:15:43,020 --> 00:15:48,030
So, my father had Medaka blood,

187
00:15:49,820 --> 00:15:56,080
and the previous chairman named him
as his successor? But then...

188
00:15:56,200 --> 00:15:59,750
We finally found Takashi Hoshi only
to discover he'd died in a car accident.

189
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:03,830
So we went to the crematorium, and saw
a sweet young girl in a sailor suit.

190
00:16:05,380 --> 00:16:06,630
And that

191
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,010
was me?

192
00:16:09,130 --> 00:16:10,170
Right.

193
00:16:11,470 --> 00:16:14,340
The previous chairman instructed that,
failing the nephew,

194
00:16:14,470 --> 00:16:16,050
we should find the next in line.

195
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:19,140
- At your service, boss.
- Chairman.

196
00:16:22,020 --> 00:16:23,440
Chairman.

197
00:16:26,770 --> 00:16:29,610
Wait a minute! Hang on!

198
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:32,320
This is absurd!

199
00:16:33,110 --> 00:16:34,570
Listen.

200
00:16:34,700 --> 00:16:38,410
I'm a high school student.
And I'm a girl, too!

201
00:16:38,540 --> 00:16:39,950
Don't worry about that.

202
00:16:40,790 --> 00:16:44,790
There are no rules on the chairman's
age or gender.

203
00:16:48,300 --> 00:16:49,340
But...

204
00:16:51,130 --> 00:16:52,550
This won't work!

205
00:16:53,340 --> 00:16:54,590
I can't do it!

206
00:16:56,430 --> 00:16:57,970
It's a whole different world.

207
00:16:58,100 --> 00:16:59,970
Everyone's a beginner at some point.

208
00:17:00,100 --> 00:17:01,730
You'll build up experience.

209
00:17:05,520 --> 00:17:06,940
Experience of what?

210
00:17:09,070 --> 00:17:10,110
Fighting?

211
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:12,070
Gambling?

212
00:17:13,450 --> 00:17:14,700
Murder?

213
00:17:16,530 --> 00:17:18,120
That kind of experience?

214
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,330
No way.

215
00:17:26,630 --> 00:17:27,880
I refuse.

216
00:17:31,510 --> 00:17:33,260
You must be kidding.

217
00:17:44,980 --> 00:17:46,520
You leave us no choice.

218
00:17:48,190 --> 00:17:49,440
I guess we have to give it up.

219
00:17:53,990 --> 00:17:55,650
This has turned into a farewell party.

220
00:17:56,740 --> 00:17:58,120
- Hiko, get the sake.
- Yes, sir.

221
00:17:58,240 --> 00:17:59,370
Mei, prepare for a raid.

222
00:17:59,490 --> 00:18:01,080
Are we going after the Matsunokis?

223
00:18:01,200 --> 00:18:05,210
If we're going to disband, we need
to at least go out with a bang.

224
00:18:05,330 --> 00:18:06,370
Gentlemen!

225
00:18:07,000 --> 00:18:09,000
- You'll die fighting with me, right?
- Yes!

226
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:13,460
You'll come to the farewell party
at least, won't you?

227
00:18:16,220 --> 00:18:17,260
But...

228
00:18:17,970 --> 00:18:20,300
If you're going to disband,

229
00:18:20,930 --> 00:18:23,310
why do you have to fight?

230
00:18:24,770 --> 00:18:27,350
It's the four of us against forty of them.

231
00:18:29,350 --> 00:18:32,400
Weren't there dozens of you
at the school gates?

232
00:18:32,520 --> 00:18:35,820
Oh, my brother just hired them
for the day.

233
00:18:35,940 --> 00:18:37,280
They're from other families.

234
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:39,160
The Medaka Family is just us four.

235
00:18:40,370 --> 00:18:42,330
Alright, let's make this official.

236
00:18:42,450 --> 00:18:43,490
Yes, Brother.

237
00:18:47,410 --> 00:18:49,330
- Dismissed!
- Brother!

238
00:18:52,420 --> 00:18:54,000
- Let's go!
- Alright!

239
00:18:54,130 --> 00:18:55,920
Let's do this!

240
00:18:56,050 --> 00:18:57,340
Wait!

241
00:19:00,430 --> 00:19:01,640
Please, wait!

242
00:19:04,140 --> 00:19:06,020
I forbid you

243
00:19:06,140 --> 00:19:07,230
to go and fight!

244
00:19:07,890 --> 00:19:10,190
What's it got to do with you?
You're not the boss!

245
00:19:12,440 --> 00:19:13,480
I

246
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:17,150
I accept your offer.

247
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:19,240
Miss...

248
00:19:19,360 --> 00:19:20,410
Therefore,

249
00:19:21,410 --> 00:19:23,620
I forbid you to go on this raid.

250
00:19:25,240 --> 00:19:26,290
Miss...

251
00:19:28,410 --> 00:19:30,420
That's "Boss" to you.

252
00:19:36,250 --> 00:19:37,460
- Boss!
- Boss!

253
00:19:39,970 --> 00:19:42,140
- Get the sake cups! Now!
- Yes!

254
00:20:01,030 --> 00:20:02,820
You're totally hungover!

255
00:20:04,320 --> 00:20:07,330
Please, not so loud!

256
00:20:09,580 --> 00:20:10,910
My head's pounding.

257
00:20:11,420 --> 00:20:13,920
I called in sick for you.

258
00:20:14,380 --> 00:20:15,840
Thanks.

259
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:19,510
You made such a scene at the school,

260
00:20:19,630 --> 00:20:22,130
they thought you'd been kidnapped
by the gangsters.

261
00:20:26,600 --> 00:20:31,140
You need to eat something.
If you don't get proper nutrition,

262
00:20:31,270 --> 00:20:33,730
your breasts and your hips
won't develop.

263
00:20:35,690 --> 00:20:37,360
My breasts are big enough, thanks.

264
00:20:41,150 --> 00:20:43,950
What's the matter? Have I done
something to offend you?

265
00:20:46,780 --> 00:20:47,830
No.

266
00:20:51,660 --> 00:20:52,710
I just don't know

267
00:20:53,420 --> 00:20:55,080
what my father

268
00:20:56,790 --> 00:20:58,250
saw in you.

269
00:21:13,940 --> 00:21:16,100
You're not especially pretty.

270
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:19,570
Nor do you seem particularly smart.

271
00:21:21,070 --> 00:21:22,570
In which case,

272
00:21:23,280 --> 00:21:25,240
it must be

273
00:21:27,370 --> 00:21:28,950
your body!

274
00:21:44,720 --> 00:21:45,880
You're silly.

275
00:21:46,890 --> 00:21:48,510
Just how many drinks did you have?

276
00:21:50,390 --> 00:21:53,810
I had about five cups of sake
around this big.

277
00:21:55,020 --> 00:21:57,900
I'm the boss, I had to drink.

278
00:21:59,110 --> 00:22:00,480
You're in trouble!

279
00:22:01,190 --> 00:22:03,990
The Medakas are real yakuza,
you know?

280
00:22:06,110 --> 00:22:07,320
Is that right?

281
00:22:09,780 --> 00:22:11,410
You know about them, Mayumi?

282
00:22:11,910 --> 00:22:12,950
Yes,

283
00:22:13,080 --> 00:22:16,710
I heard of them back
in my degenerate days.

284
00:22:19,500 --> 00:22:20,790
I'm worried about you.

285
00:22:27,510 --> 00:22:29,890
Sorry to drag you out like this, Boss.

286
00:22:31,180 --> 00:22:33,680
So who are we going to introduce me to?

287
00:22:33,810 --> 00:22:34,850
Pardon?

288
00:22:34,980 --> 00:22:36,430
Where are we going?

289
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:39,520
To see the Hamaguchi Family's
chairman.

290
00:22:40,270 --> 00:22:42,570
They're the biggest family in the area.

291
00:22:43,610 --> 00:22:44,940
What a pain!

292
00:22:45,940 --> 00:22:48,360
I don't know any yakuza etiquette.

293
00:22:48,910 --> 00:22:52,700
"It's an honor to meet you, sir!"
Like that, right?

294
00:23:00,630 --> 00:23:03,170
All yakuza have a front these days.

295
00:23:04,550 --> 00:23:08,090
Every chairman is the president
of some company or other.

296
00:23:19,730 --> 00:23:21,770
What's that on our roof?

297
00:23:22,230 --> 00:23:23,440
Graves.

298
00:23:33,740 --> 00:23:35,620
Do they always keep you
waiting this long?

299
00:23:37,000 --> 00:23:38,080
Be patient!

300
00:23:38,870 --> 00:23:41,080
If we offend them, we're done for.

301
00:23:41,580 --> 00:23:42,920
Is the boss in?

302
00:23:43,040 --> 00:23:44,670
Yes, please wait just a moment.

303
00:23:47,760 --> 00:23:51,130
They look scary! Who is he?

304
00:23:52,010 --> 00:23:54,140
That's Sekine, the Matsunoki chairman.

305
00:23:55,810 --> 00:23:57,640
The Matsunokis?

306
00:23:57,770 --> 00:23:59,810
Weren't they the ones
you were going to fight?

307
00:24:00,560 --> 00:24:02,350
They're affiliated with the Hamaguchis.

308
00:24:02,480 --> 00:24:04,810
That's why they're infringing
on our territory.

309
00:24:08,440 --> 00:24:09,950
That you, Sakuma?

310
00:24:13,660 --> 00:24:14,870
Hello.

311
00:24:14,990 --> 00:24:16,700
How's business?

312
00:24:16,830 --> 00:24:18,290
- Can't complain.
- Really?

313
00:24:19,330 --> 00:24:21,750
This is our fourth chairman.

314
00:24:24,960 --> 00:24:26,750
Stop pulling my leg!

315
00:24:31,260 --> 00:24:34,390
I'm Izumi Hoshi, fourth chairman
of the Medaka Family.

316
00:24:35,050 --> 00:24:36,100
Nice to meet you.

317
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:39,390
"Nice to meet you"? Get a load of her!

318
00:24:41,600 --> 00:24:43,940
What is this, an internship?

319
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:45,520
Huh, Sakuma?

320
00:24:46,150 --> 00:24:49,030
You expect this little girl
to run your family?

321
00:24:50,240 --> 00:24:52,570
You couldn't even sell her
to a bathhouse.

322
00:24:52,700 --> 00:24:55,280
Go home and change your diaper!

323
00:24:55,410 --> 00:24:56,450
Say that again.

324
00:24:57,830 --> 00:25:00,080
Insult our chairman again
and you're dead.

325
00:25:00,200 --> 00:25:02,080
Whoa, whoa! Easy, now!

326
00:25:02,210 --> 00:25:04,500
Don't be like that. It's just a joke.

327
00:25:07,750 --> 00:25:09,550
Now I look more closely, though,

328
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:13,590
don't you have a pretty little face?

329
00:25:13,720 --> 00:25:15,260
I could just eat you up!

330
00:25:18,390 --> 00:25:19,430
You little bitch!

331
00:25:20,020 --> 00:25:21,060
<i>Hold it!</i>

332
00:25:21,600 --> 00:25:22,640
<i>Sekine!</i>

333
00:25:23,100 --> 00:25:24,480
<i>Come to my office, now.</i>

334
00:25:25,730 --> 00:25:28,020
<i>And bring our guests
from the Medaka Family.</i>

335
00:25:28,150 --> 00:25:29,230
Right away, sir.

336
00:25:34,490 --> 00:25:35,530
Boss.

337
00:26:38,590 --> 00:26:39,890
I like you.

338
00:26:40,890 --> 00:26:43,470
You have guts, and you're cute.

339
00:26:44,220 --> 00:26:47,020
I can see why you're at the head
of the Medaka Family.

340
00:26:48,060 --> 00:26:49,900
I really like you.

341
00:26:54,190 --> 00:26:55,240
Boss.

342
00:27:03,950 --> 00:27:05,620
Stop goofing around!

343
00:27:05,750 --> 00:27:07,000
Brother! Brother!

344
00:27:07,120 --> 00:27:10,880
Are we really getting back the turf
the Matsunokis took from us?

345
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:13,130
It's a gift from the Hamaguchis
for the new boss!

346
00:27:13,250 --> 00:27:14,710
This is great!

347
00:27:14,840 --> 00:27:15,880
To the new chairman!

348
00:27:16,010 --> 00:27:17,470
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

349
00:27:19,840 --> 00:27:21,890
Move it! Brother...

350
00:27:22,010 --> 00:27:23,050
Not again...

351
00:27:23,850 --> 00:27:25,560
What's the matter with you?

352
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:29,690
We haven't had so much fun in years.

353
00:27:29,810 --> 00:27:31,020
I'm just so happy!

354
00:27:32,230 --> 00:27:33,980
I'm sorry things have been so bad.

355
00:27:34,110 --> 00:27:37,610
Not you too, Brother!
This is a new beginning for the Medakas.

356
00:27:37,740 --> 00:27:40,160
Exactly! So don't cry, Brother!

357
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:42,240
Yes, this is a new beginning!

358
00:27:44,530 --> 00:27:45,700
Attention!

359
00:27:45,830 --> 00:27:49,580
Cheer up, everyone! Yakuza don't cry!

360
00:27:49,710 --> 00:27:51,080
Understood?

361
00:27:51,210 --> 00:27:52,500
- Yes, Boss!
- Yes, Boss!

362
00:27:52,630 --> 00:27:53,670
Good!

363
00:27:58,460 --> 00:27:59,510
What's happening?

364
00:27:59,630 --> 00:28:00,680
Machine guns.

365
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:04,390
What do we do?

366
00:28:04,510 --> 00:28:06,470
Get the weapons, you idiot!

367
00:28:06,600 --> 00:28:08,600
Mei, get the weapons!

368
00:28:08,730 --> 00:28:09,770
Now!

369
00:28:11,900 --> 00:28:12,940
Brother!

370
00:28:15,360 --> 00:28:16,440
Brother!

371
00:28:16,570 --> 00:28:17,690
<i>I've been expelled!</i>

372
00:28:18,940 --> 00:28:20,150
- Izumi!
- Izumi!

373
00:28:22,910 --> 00:28:24,200
Izumi!

374
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:27,450
We've started a petition
to let you come back to school!

375
00:28:37,840 --> 00:28:39,340
Don't let the bastards get you down!

376
00:28:51,940 --> 00:28:53,600
Izumi Hoshi?

377
00:28:56,310 --> 00:28:57,860
Yes?

378
00:28:59,150 --> 00:29:01,690
I'm Kuroki, Shinjuku Police Department.

379
00:29:03,360 --> 00:29:05,570
- You're a detective?
- Yes.

380
00:29:08,080 --> 00:29:10,660
- Is this about what happened yesterday?
- Yesterday?

381
00:29:12,910 --> 00:29:13,960
No?

382
00:29:14,670 --> 00:29:18,340
I wanted to talk to you
about your late father.

383
00:29:19,920 --> 00:29:21,170
My father?

384
00:29:29,930 --> 00:29:33,640
He was hit by a truck at the airport
on his way back from a business trip?

385
00:29:35,480 --> 00:29:36,900
That's what I was told.

386
00:29:37,860 --> 00:29:41,150
He had already died
by the time the police called me.

387
00:29:41,730 --> 00:29:45,410
Actually, it seems someone forced
his car into the truck's path.

388
00:29:47,780 --> 00:29:49,580
You mean,

389
00:29:51,080 --> 00:29:52,950
he was murdered?

390
00:29:55,670 --> 00:29:57,880
- He worked for a trading company?
- Yes.

391
00:29:58,000 --> 00:30:00,130
- Did he travel overseas much?
- All the time.

392
00:30:00,670 --> 00:30:03,760
Did he ever bring home any souvenirs?

393
00:30:04,800 --> 00:30:08,930
Like small packages, about this big?

394
00:30:09,050 --> 00:30:10,100
No.

395
00:30:13,020 --> 00:30:15,140
What exactly are you trying to find out?

396
00:30:15,640 --> 00:30:17,980
Well, when there's a murder
at an airport,

397
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:21,150
in most cases, smuggling is involved.

398
00:30:23,070 --> 00:30:24,110
Smuggling?

399
00:30:28,360 --> 00:30:32,160
You think my father was a smuggler?

400
00:30:35,580 --> 00:30:38,120
That's impossible! You must be joking.

401
00:30:39,830 --> 00:30:40,880
I apologize.

402
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:45,130
It's just it's a detective job
to suspect everything.

403
00:30:45,670 --> 00:30:46,880
It's not nice, I know.

404
00:30:47,970 --> 00:30:50,220
I believe what you say about your father.

405
00:30:50,350 --> 00:30:51,720
Well, I'll be going.

406
00:30:51,850 --> 00:30:56,930
Oh, I went by your apartment,
and there was a woman there.

407
00:30:57,060 --> 00:30:58,100
Who is she?

408
00:30:59,850 --> 00:31:01,110
You mean Mayumi?

409
00:31:03,110 --> 00:31:04,150
She's a relative.

410
00:31:04,900 --> 00:31:06,580
It would be too lonely if I was on my own.

411
00:31:09,990 --> 00:31:11,570
Is something wrong?

412
00:31:11,700 --> 00:31:15,040
I've seen her before.
On a wanted poster, I think.

413
00:31:15,160 --> 00:31:16,790
Her real name is Tsunemi Tsuchida.

414
00:31:17,290 --> 00:31:20,830
She has a history of theft, prostitution,
shoplifting, you name it.

415
00:31:21,580 --> 00:31:23,880
I'm probably mistaken.
Alright, see you later!

416
00:32:04,750 --> 00:32:05,920
You gave me a scare!

417
00:32:06,500 --> 00:32:07,960
I just got back to the station

418
00:32:08,090 --> 00:32:10,050
and I heard you called the police!

419
00:32:11,430 --> 00:32:12,470
Sorry.

420
00:32:29,860 --> 00:32:31,950
My goodness!

421
00:32:34,490 --> 00:32:36,700
This is the work of a professional.

422
00:32:37,540 --> 00:32:41,000
I doubt they left any prints for us.

423
00:32:41,120 --> 00:32:42,960
Where's that woman?

424
00:32:45,710 --> 00:32:46,880
She's gone.

425
00:32:48,460 --> 00:32:50,880
It was like this when I got home.

426
00:32:54,180 --> 00:32:57,720
Strange. Is she really a relative?

427
00:33:01,060 --> 00:33:03,190
She had a letter from my father.

428
00:33:05,150 --> 00:33:06,810
Telling her to live with me.

429
00:33:06,940 --> 00:33:10,440
Telling her to live with you?
It gets even stranger.

430
00:33:10,570 --> 00:33:14,070
But why would they make all this mess
and not take anything?

431
00:33:15,240 --> 00:33:17,030
They weren't after money.

432
00:33:17,660 --> 00:33:19,080
Whoever did this,

433
00:33:19,200 --> 00:33:24,000
they were doing a very thorough search
for something hidden.

434
00:33:24,580 --> 00:33:26,290
But they didn't find it?

435
00:33:27,460 --> 00:33:31,340
If they did, there would be no need
to turn the place upside down, right?

436
00:33:31,840 --> 00:33:35,130
Very good! You're a sharp one.
That's exactly what I think.

437
00:33:38,970 --> 00:33:42,100
What were they looking for, then?

438
00:33:42,230 --> 00:33:45,100
Drugs, maybe.

439
00:33:46,230 --> 00:33:47,440
Drugs?

440
00:33:50,150 --> 00:33:51,650
It's just a joke.

441
00:33:52,360 --> 00:33:54,150
He's teasing us.

442
00:33:57,950 --> 00:34:00,660
Sorry, but this is no joke.

443
00:34:03,540 --> 00:34:05,290
Your father was a drug trafficker.

444
00:34:14,420 --> 00:34:15,550
Dad was?

445
00:34:17,550 --> 00:34:21,470
I spoke with someone
from the Tokyo Police's narcotics team.

446
00:34:22,010 --> 00:34:24,890
I asked him to check the files,
just to be sure.

447
00:34:26,350 --> 00:34:31,190
They've had their eye on Takashi Hoshi
for a long time.

448
00:34:38,570 --> 00:34:39,780
Should I continue?

449
00:34:41,450 --> 00:34:42,490
Go ahead.

450
00:34:49,000 --> 00:34:52,670
Actually, I better say no more.

451
00:34:53,380 --> 00:34:54,800
It doesn't feel right.

452
00:34:57,130 --> 00:34:58,470
Please carry on!

453
00:34:58,590 --> 00:34:59,760
You don't need to pity me!

454
00:34:59,890 --> 00:35:03,100
This is bad, guys! He's hitting on Izumi!

455
00:35:03,220 --> 00:35:06,100
What should we do?
We have to do something.

456
00:35:06,230 --> 00:35:09,150
I don't think it's anything
to worry about. He's a cop.

457
00:35:09,270 --> 00:35:12,320
You're such a sucker. Cops are still men.

458
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:13,940
Which means he's a rival.

459
00:35:14,070 --> 00:35:16,860
Any guy who tries to get near Izumi
is our enemy!

460
00:35:17,740 --> 00:35:19,450
Take a closer look.

461
00:35:19,570 --> 00:35:21,620
They're all friendly with each other!

462
00:35:23,330 --> 00:35:27,960
Your father used his business trips
to bring drugs back to Japan.

463
00:35:28,960 --> 00:35:32,460
There's no question that he did this
so that he could sell them.

464
00:35:33,710 --> 00:35:36,630
Someone decided they wanted to take
these drugs for themselves,

465
00:35:36,760 --> 00:35:38,510
and murdered him at the airport.

466
00:35:38,970 --> 00:35:43,850
However, they couldn't find the drugs
either among your father's belongings

467
00:35:43,970 --> 00:35:46,720
or at your home.

468
00:35:47,730 --> 00:35:49,100
Do you know this for sure?

469
00:35:49,890 --> 00:35:50,940
It's conjecture.

470
00:35:51,730 --> 00:35:54,860
When you start joining the dots,

471
00:35:54,980 --> 00:35:56,610
it leads to this conclusion.

472
00:35:57,110 --> 00:35:58,570
You sound very sure of yourself.

473
00:36:00,530 --> 00:36:01,740
Disagreeably so.

474
00:36:04,080 --> 00:36:05,830
I'm a disagreeable cop.

475
00:36:07,120 --> 00:36:09,500
The kind of disagreeable cop
who won't shut up

476
00:36:09,620 --> 00:36:13,170
when he knows his theories
are upsetting a young girl.

477
00:36:18,090 --> 00:36:20,220
Oh! That smile says this is nothing!

478
00:36:21,550 --> 00:36:22,930
You're a tough girl, aren't you?

479
00:36:24,350 --> 00:36:26,470
I'd be lying if I said
this didn't upset me.

480
00:36:26,970 --> 00:36:28,350
But I'm alright.

481
00:36:29,520 --> 00:36:31,480
I feel like I can
get through this somehow.

482
00:36:32,060 --> 00:36:33,350
That's good to know.

483
00:36:34,190 --> 00:36:35,400
Hi!

484
00:36:35,520 --> 00:36:36,610
Who are they?

485
00:36:36,730 --> 00:36:37,820
Drunks?

486
00:36:37,940 --> 00:36:39,860
Don't mind them. They're just my men.

487
00:36:40,570 --> 00:36:41,610
Huh?

488
00:36:42,410 --> 00:36:43,700
I forgot to say.

489
00:36:43,820 --> 00:36:48,370
Izumi Hoshi, fourth chairman
of the Medaka Family of Kanto.

490
00:36:58,420 --> 00:37:01,670
He got so jealous

491
00:37:01,800 --> 00:37:05,300
that he said he was going to kill him!

492
00:37:06,550 --> 00:37:08,640
He didn't expect him to be a cop!

493
00:37:09,720 --> 00:37:14,480
"You're so cute, Boss! I love you!"

494
00:37:14,600 --> 00:37:16,520
Shut your trap, asshole!

495
00:37:16,650 --> 00:37:18,570
- You're blushing!
- Come here!

496
00:37:18,690 --> 00:37:19,900
Are you for real?

497
00:37:20,400 --> 00:37:22,280
- She's way out of your league!
- Come back!

498
00:37:22,400 --> 00:37:23,450
What a fool!

499
00:37:24,820 --> 00:37:28,330
Listen, you all need to brighten up!

500
00:37:28,910 --> 00:37:32,500
Looking at you all glum like that
is a real buzzkill!

501
00:37:32,620 --> 00:37:34,830
Have a drink!

502
00:37:35,330 --> 00:37:37,290
No, they're underage!

503
00:37:38,710 --> 00:37:41,260
You don't get a choice! Now drink up!

504
00:37:41,380 --> 00:37:43,470
Hurry up! Take it!

505
00:37:43,590 --> 00:37:45,930
- Alright, I'll drink.
- Good!

506
00:37:46,050 --> 00:37:48,140
Just watch me!

507
00:37:48,260 --> 00:37:49,890
That's more like it!

508
00:37:52,220 --> 00:37:55,390
What did I tell you?

509
00:37:55,520 --> 00:37:58,270
It burns... I'm going to die...

510
00:37:58,400 --> 00:37:59,940
Like hell you are!

511
00:38:01,190 --> 00:38:03,240
I don't want to die a virgin!

512
00:38:03,360 --> 00:38:04,700
Virgin?

513
00:38:05,280 --> 00:38:09,580
- Virgin? What a nostalgic word!
- Hey! Hey!

514
00:38:09,700 --> 00:38:11,160
Go on, Mei.

515
00:38:11,290 --> 00:38:16,500
The first time I went to a bathhouse,
it was my first semester at junior high!

516
00:38:16,620 --> 00:38:19,340
You're weird! What an idiot.

517
00:38:19,460 --> 00:38:22,130
You only got laid because you
forced yourself on someone!

518
00:38:22,250 --> 00:38:24,050
- You little prick!
- Hey! Hey!

519
00:38:24,510 --> 00:38:27,010
You guys can be so brash sometimes.

520
00:38:27,470 --> 00:38:30,220
You're even spoiling the mood for me.

521
00:38:30,850 --> 00:38:32,640
We'll be more careful from now on.

522
00:38:33,890 --> 00:38:36,940
Izumi! We're going to call it a night now.

523
00:38:37,560 --> 00:38:38,600
You are?

524
00:38:39,100 --> 00:38:42,270
Stay at my place if you want.
I have plenty of spare rooms.

525
00:38:43,570 --> 00:38:45,490
I'll pass, thanks.

526
00:38:45,610 --> 00:38:46,900
Why?

527
00:38:47,030 --> 00:38:51,580
No reason in particular!
I just want to keep partying.

528
00:38:52,030 --> 00:38:53,410
I don't want to be alone.

529
00:38:54,290 --> 00:38:55,620
If I'm left by myself tonight,

530
00:38:55,750 --> 00:38:59,960
I'll end up going crazy
and looking like this.

531
00:39:00,460 --> 00:39:04,550
And girls don't like
to be seen looking like that.

532
00:39:04,670 --> 00:39:06,050
I get it.

533
00:39:06,170 --> 00:39:10,260
No, I don't want you to get it.

534
00:39:10,390 --> 00:39:15,810
Men and women are different, you see.
You'd never understand.

535
00:39:16,680 --> 00:39:17,810
Izumi!

536
00:39:20,150 --> 00:39:22,570
Thanks! Good night.

537
00:39:22,690 --> 00:39:24,400
- Good night!
- Izumi!

538
00:39:24,530 --> 00:39:25,650
Night!

539
00:39:25,780 --> 00:39:29,820
Go home, take a dump,
and get to bed, like a good kid!

540
00:39:29,950 --> 00:39:31,240
Dumbass!

541
00:39:34,990 --> 00:39:36,370
- Hey, Hiko!
- What?

542
00:39:36,500 --> 00:39:38,790
- I want to ride a motorbike.
- A motorbike?

543
00:39:38,910 --> 00:39:41,540
I want the wind to blow away
my troubles!

544
00:39:41,670 --> 00:39:43,170
You got it!

545
00:39:44,170 --> 00:39:47,670
Mei, Mei. The boss said
she'd go crazy tonight.

546
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:48,840
What does that mean?

547
00:39:48,970 --> 00:39:50,300
I don't know.

548
00:39:50,430 --> 00:39:53,930
Stop! It's me!

549
00:39:54,050 --> 00:39:55,350
Hey, watch it!

550
00:39:55,470 --> 00:39:57,180
Look! It's me!

551
00:39:57,310 --> 00:40:00,810
- Hey! Are you well?
- Of course I am. Now give me the bike!

552
00:40:00,940 --> 00:40:02,060
Sure, she's all yours.

553
00:40:03,150 --> 00:40:04,690
Hop on, Boss!

554
00:40:04,820 --> 00:40:06,440
Get her a helmet!

555
00:40:06,570 --> 00:40:07,610
That'll do.

556
00:40:11,240 --> 00:40:12,410
Perfect!

557
00:40:12,530 --> 00:40:13,700
Hold on! Here we go!

558
00:40:13,820 --> 00:40:16,040
- Let's go!
- Alright!

559
00:41:24,600 --> 00:41:25,770
I'm cold!

560
00:41:26,440 --> 00:41:27,770
Boss!

561
00:41:27,900 --> 00:41:28,940
Boss!

562
00:41:30,400 --> 00:41:31,780
What?

563
00:41:31,900 --> 00:41:34,070
I think I felt the rain on my back.

564
00:41:34,200 --> 00:41:36,820
You'll catch a cold hanging on to me.

565
00:41:38,030 --> 00:41:39,540
It's alright.

566
00:41:39,990 --> 00:41:41,120
It stopped raining.

567
00:41:41,250 --> 00:41:42,710
What? It stopped?

568
00:41:43,790 --> 00:41:45,420
Yes!

569
00:41:45,540 --> 00:41:47,500
This feels great!

570
00:41:48,250 --> 00:41:50,090
I'll speed up, then!

571
00:41:57,390 --> 00:41:58,600
- Hiko.
- Yeah?

572
00:41:59,680 --> 00:42:01,890
Why did you join the Medaka Family?

573
00:42:02,810 --> 00:42:05,060
No reason, really!

574
00:42:06,020 --> 00:42:09,190
Yes there is!
Answer the chairman's question.

575
00:42:09,310 --> 00:42:10,610
In 100 words or less!

576
00:42:11,730 --> 00:42:14,700
There wasn't any line of work
I was suited to.

577
00:42:16,570 --> 00:42:20,200
I hated school.
And I hated working even more!

578
00:42:20,330 --> 00:42:24,460
After the biker gang, being a yakuza
was the natural next step!

579
00:42:25,250 --> 00:42:28,210
What can I say? My career
was destined for great things!

580
00:42:53,190 --> 00:42:55,860
- Over here, over here.
- Hey, Mei. Is there any order to this?

581
00:42:55,990 --> 00:42:57,650
Yes, the red one goes in the middle.

582
00:42:57,780 --> 00:42:58,820
Red one in the middle...

583
00:43:00,660 --> 00:43:01,990
Good morning, Boss!

584
00:43:02,120 --> 00:43:03,160
Oh, good morning!

585
00:43:03,290 --> 00:43:04,370
Good morning!

586
00:43:07,750 --> 00:43:09,040
What on earth are you doing?

587
00:43:09,170 --> 00:43:13,840
We're redecorating so that you
feel more at home here, Boss.

588
00:43:16,510 --> 00:43:18,300
- Coffee.
- Coming right up!

589
00:43:18,430 --> 00:43:19,680
Boss!

590
00:43:19,800 --> 00:43:22,850
Mei picked everything out.
Doesn't he have good taste?

591
00:43:23,810 --> 00:43:25,350
Brilliant taste!

592
00:43:25,470 --> 00:43:30,230
I used to be a decorator.
I just used what I learned from that.

593
00:43:32,560 --> 00:43:35,530
We have money to renovate?

594
00:43:35,650 --> 00:43:38,200
Thanks to you,
we're making more money now.

595
00:43:39,280 --> 00:43:41,030
Your coffee, Boss.

596
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:44,330
Would you like it here, or at your desk?

597
00:43:46,830 --> 00:43:48,750
Boss! Hey.

598
00:43:49,410 --> 00:43:51,210
Try it out, Boss!

599
00:43:57,710 --> 00:43:59,420
Would you like milk, Boss?

600
00:43:59,880 --> 00:44:01,180
- Yes, please.
- Okay!

601
00:44:05,390 --> 00:44:06,970
Wait, where's Hiko?

602
00:44:07,100 --> 00:44:08,850
Huh? You don't know either, Boss?

603
00:44:09,430 --> 00:44:11,940
I haven't seen him
since he took me home last night.

604
00:44:12,060 --> 00:44:13,310
He's like a bullet.

605
00:44:13,440 --> 00:44:15,070
He doesn't come back!

606
00:44:15,900 --> 00:44:17,730
I'll get it!

607
00:44:17,860 --> 00:44:19,070
Medaka Family.

608
00:44:19,190 --> 00:44:20,570
Yes, that's right.

609
00:44:21,200 --> 00:44:22,240
Huh?

610
00:44:25,120 --> 00:44:26,160
Hello?

611
00:44:26,740 --> 00:44:27,790
Hello?

612
00:44:29,370 --> 00:44:30,410
What was that?

613
00:44:30,540 --> 00:44:32,960
Some strange guy. He said,
"The goods are on the stairs."

614
00:44:33,080 --> 00:44:34,420
What goods?

615
00:44:34,540 --> 00:44:36,040
- Go check.
- Alright.

616
00:44:36,670 --> 00:44:37,800
Here you go, Brother!

617
00:44:39,010 --> 00:44:41,380
I don't suppose it's a bomb or something.

618
00:44:41,930 --> 00:44:44,390
After the machine gun?
Too much of a step down.

619
00:44:47,100 --> 00:44:48,850
Hiko!

620
00:44:49,980 --> 00:44:51,890
Hiko!

621
00:44:52,020 --> 00:44:53,060
Hiko!

622
00:44:56,270 --> 00:44:57,690
The Matsunokis did this!

623
00:44:59,190 --> 00:45:00,650
First the machine gun,

624
00:45:01,360 --> 00:45:03,240
now they're taking us out one by one.

625
00:45:05,160 --> 00:45:08,450
Hiko, we'll avenge you.

626
00:45:11,620 --> 00:45:13,500
They shot at us on our own turf,

627
00:45:15,630 --> 00:45:17,750
and now they've killed one of us!

628
00:45:18,590 --> 00:45:21,720
I can't just sit back and take this!

629
00:45:23,380 --> 00:45:24,890
I mean it!

630
00:45:25,010 --> 00:45:26,050
Boss!

631
00:45:27,470 --> 00:45:30,060
- Boss!
- What's all this racket?

632
00:45:31,230 --> 00:45:33,190
Keep it down, will you?

633
00:45:35,020 --> 00:45:37,020
That's very dear to me! Bastard!

634
00:45:37,150 --> 00:45:38,190
Boss!

635
00:45:40,360 --> 00:45:41,400
Boss!

636
00:45:42,820 --> 00:45:43,860
Boss...

637
00:45:44,490 --> 00:45:46,450
- Idiot!
- Boss.

638
00:45:47,410 --> 00:45:48,830
- Where are you going?
- Let me go!

639
00:45:48,950 --> 00:45:49,990
- Boss!
- Boss!

640
00:45:52,580 --> 00:45:54,670
You've got balls,
coming here on your own.

641
00:45:56,290 --> 00:46:00,340
I want to have an honest discussion,
chairman to chairman.

642
00:46:04,840 --> 00:46:06,760
One of my men was killed.

643
00:46:08,430 --> 00:46:09,850
But you know that.

644
00:46:09,970 --> 00:46:11,930
Yes. I do.

645
00:46:13,980 --> 00:46:15,730
That's why I'm here.

646
00:46:19,480 --> 00:46:21,480
The Matsunoki Family did it.

647
00:46:23,150 --> 00:46:24,190
Damned imbecile!

648
00:46:25,280 --> 00:46:26,860
Don't say such slanderous things.

649
00:46:29,200 --> 00:46:32,120
Listen to me, little girl.

650
00:46:33,250 --> 00:46:35,910
It was us who shot up your office, yes.

651
00:46:37,080 --> 00:46:41,040
But after that, the head
of the Hamaguchis gave orders

652
00:46:41,170 --> 00:46:43,760
not to lay a finger on the Medaka Family.

653
00:46:45,170 --> 00:46:48,010
Any more incidents would get us
too much unwanted attention.

654
00:46:48,890 --> 00:46:51,430
This is inconveniencing us, too!

655
00:46:52,600 --> 00:46:53,850
Do you understand?

656
00:46:58,770 --> 00:46:59,860
Yes, sir.

657
00:47:05,360 --> 00:47:07,150
I just wanted to make sure.

658
00:47:07,860 --> 00:47:09,240
Goodbye.

659
00:47:09,360 --> 00:47:10,570
Not so fast.

660
00:47:13,040 --> 00:47:16,290
Teach this impudent little girl
some manners.

661
00:47:16,410 --> 00:47:17,460
- Yes, Boss!
- Yes, Boss!

662
00:47:19,790 --> 00:47:20,960
Pipe down!

663
00:47:21,540 --> 00:47:23,000
Shut up!

664
00:47:35,850 --> 00:47:39,190
Fourth Chairman!
Your clothes are all dirty!

665
00:47:45,980 --> 00:47:48,610
Just dunk her up to her head already!

666
00:47:50,530 --> 00:47:52,990
- Chairman!
- How's the temperature?

667
00:47:53,120 --> 00:47:55,080
I'd like to take a dip myself!

668
00:47:56,620 --> 00:47:58,160
Sekine speaking!

669
00:47:59,410 --> 00:48:01,710
What? You have my boy?

670
00:48:03,090 --> 00:48:05,420
Daddy! Help me, Daddy!

671
00:48:06,880 --> 00:48:09,130
If there's so much as a scratch
on our chairman

672
00:48:09,260 --> 00:48:11,720
your halfwit of a son is history.

673
00:48:12,470 --> 00:48:13,800
Tell him again!

674
00:48:13,930 --> 00:48:15,510
Daddy!

675
00:48:15,640 --> 00:48:17,680
Don't die on us! We need you.

676
00:48:19,100 --> 00:48:20,230
Here, talk to him.

677
00:48:25,070 --> 00:48:27,320
Let me down already!

678
00:48:28,030 --> 00:48:29,400
Stop!

679
00:48:29,530 --> 00:48:31,150
Stop, stop!

680
00:48:31,610 --> 00:48:33,490
Hey, the boss said to stop.

681
00:48:34,660 --> 00:48:36,080
Stop!

682
00:48:36,200 --> 00:48:38,580
- Stop!
- Bring her down!

683
00:48:38,700 --> 00:48:39,700
Bring her down!

684
00:48:44,420 --> 00:48:45,500
I'll move this.

685
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:47,210
- Okay?
- Yeah.

686
00:48:53,760 --> 00:48:54,800
Well?

687
00:48:55,550 --> 00:48:58,470
I think you've got a taste for
how fearsome the yakuza can be.

688
00:49:01,520 --> 00:49:02,980
Yes, I was scared.

689
00:49:04,400 --> 00:49:07,400
But it's only made me more determined!

690
00:49:09,320 --> 00:49:11,650
Until we get Hiko's killer,

691
00:49:13,990 --> 00:49:16,240
I won't stop fighting!

692
00:49:16,370 --> 00:49:17,660
I was waiting for that!

693
00:49:18,580 --> 00:49:22,370
You've got a pretty face, but that
yakuza blood makes you a fighter!

694
00:49:22,500 --> 00:49:23,710
The girl's got spunk.

695
00:49:25,420 --> 00:49:26,460
What's your problem?

696
00:49:27,500 --> 00:49:32,720
I just don't think, as a girl, she should
be getting any deeper into this.

697
00:49:32,840 --> 00:49:35,090
She's not a girl. She's the chairman!

698
00:49:35,220 --> 00:49:38,430
Our brother's dead, and you want us
to lie back and take it?

699
00:49:38,560 --> 00:49:41,810
But we had such a close call today!

700
00:49:45,310 --> 00:49:47,480
We best make a grave for Hiko.

701
00:49:58,830 --> 00:50:02,500
Boss, have you ever heard
of someone called Fatso?

702
00:50:03,750 --> 00:50:05,460
- Fatso?
- Yeah.

703
00:50:06,790 --> 00:50:10,300
His real name is Hajime Sandaiji.
He's the leader of another yakuza family.

704
00:50:12,130 --> 00:50:13,170
What about him?

705
00:50:14,880 --> 00:50:18,510
I can't think of anyone else
capable of such brutality.

706
00:50:21,640 --> 00:50:23,520
But why?

707
00:50:27,060 --> 00:50:28,100
For drugs.

708
00:50:29,940 --> 00:50:33,940
Whenever a deal's going down,
Fatso is always involved somehow.

709
00:50:35,820 --> 00:50:38,280
He's after your father's drugs.

710
00:50:38,950 --> 00:50:43,160
But even after ransacking
your apartment, he found nothing.

711
00:50:45,540 --> 00:50:48,000
So he tortured Hiko
to try to make him talk.

712
00:50:55,300 --> 00:50:57,630
But there are no drugs!

713
00:50:57,760 --> 00:50:59,050
There must be.

714
00:51:00,430 --> 00:51:03,850
If Fatso's sticking his nose in,
there must be drugs somewhere.

715
00:51:08,940 --> 00:51:09,980
Boss.

716
00:51:13,280 --> 00:51:14,690
You have to be careful.

717
00:51:16,030 --> 00:51:17,860
Don't do anything reckless again.

718
00:51:19,990 --> 00:51:21,450
Reckless?

719
00:51:21,580 --> 00:51:24,120
Like going to take on
the Matsunoki Family alone.

720
00:51:28,290 --> 00:51:29,750
I did it for Hiko!

721
00:51:30,710 --> 00:51:32,840
Don't you care that he was killed?

722
00:51:32,960 --> 00:51:34,170
Of course I do!

723
00:51:36,920 --> 00:51:38,720
But unlike me,

724
00:51:40,140 --> 00:51:44,390
no one can replace you, Boss.

725
00:51:46,020 --> 00:51:47,680
That's so cold!

726
00:51:48,640 --> 00:51:49,730
That's awful!

727
00:51:51,940 --> 00:51:53,980
So this is the kind of person
you are, Sakuma?

728
00:52:22,640 --> 00:52:24,140
Leave me alone.

729
00:52:24,260 --> 00:52:28,480
No can do, I'm afraid. Brother Sakuma
asked me to make sure you're safe.

730
00:52:31,390 --> 00:52:32,730
I'm fine.

731
00:52:34,770 --> 00:52:36,570
I'll walk you home!

732
00:54:25,220 --> 00:54:26,260
Hello?

733
00:54:26,720 --> 00:54:28,220
Hoshi residence.

734
00:54:32,720 --> 00:54:33,770
Hello?

735
00:54:36,770 --> 00:54:38,150
<i>Izumi?</i>

736
00:54:43,230 --> 00:54:44,570
Yes, Izumi Hoshi speaking.

737
00:54:46,490 --> 00:54:49,490
<i>It's me, Mayumi.</i>

738
00:54:51,740 --> 00:54:54,790
<i>It's been a while, and I wondered
how you were doing!</i>

739
00:54:55,500 --> 00:54:57,750
<i>Are you getting on alright by yourself?</i>

740
00:54:59,080 --> 00:55:00,420
I'm fine.

741
00:55:00,540 --> 00:55:01,880
<i>Good!</i>

742
00:55:03,250 --> 00:55:04,300
<i>That's really good.</i>

743
00:55:09,970 --> 00:55:12,180
Did you want something?

744
00:55:13,430 --> 00:55:18,140
<i>Well, I'm surviving, I suppose.</i>

745
00:55:19,940 --> 00:55:22,770
<i>I thought you must be wondering
why I disappeared so suddenly,</i>

746
00:55:23,480 --> 00:55:25,400
<i>so I decided to give you a call.</i>

747
00:55:26,490 --> 00:55:28,360
<i>But you seem to be doing just great.</i>

748
00:55:33,830 --> 00:55:35,540
Not really.

749
00:55:39,290 --> 00:55:41,920
I hate everything.

750
00:55:43,170 --> 00:55:44,210
<i>Really?</i>

751
00:55:45,710 --> 00:55:47,300
<i>So you're feeling down, huh?</i>

752
00:55:49,630 --> 00:55:51,220
<i>I'd like to see you.</i>

753
00:55:52,720 --> 00:55:54,600
<i>There's something I'd like to ask</i>

754
00:55:56,980 --> 00:55:58,730
<i>your forgiveness for.</i>

755
00:56:02,900 --> 00:56:06,110
I started hanging out in places
like this when I was in grade school.

756
00:56:06,730 --> 00:56:08,860
My mother ran a bar,

757
00:56:09,740 --> 00:56:11,360
so I became an alcoholic in junior high

758
00:56:11,490 --> 00:56:13,200
and a junkie in high school.

759
00:56:13,320 --> 00:56:14,620
When I got to college...

760
00:56:14,740 --> 00:56:17,000
Yes, I went to college, believe it or not.

761
00:56:17,660 --> 00:56:19,290
I majored in pharmacy,

762
00:56:20,290 --> 00:56:23,000
because I thought I could get my hands
on anything I wanted.

763
00:56:23,130 --> 00:56:25,380
But I was naive.

764
00:56:26,300 --> 00:56:29,550
I ended up getting caught
stealing heroin.

765
00:56:30,090 --> 00:56:32,760
That was my life over, there and then.

766
00:56:33,890 --> 00:56:36,930
I had more men than I can remember.

767
00:56:37,850 --> 00:56:39,390
Life was nothing but pain.

768
00:56:41,480 --> 00:56:44,020
I was drunk and high
when I crashed my car.

769
00:56:45,360 --> 00:56:47,070
It was raining so heavily.

770
00:56:50,950 --> 00:56:56,330
Then a car came past, and the driver
saved me. I was half dead.

771
00:56:57,410 --> 00:56:59,200
That was Takashi Hoshi.

772
00:57:00,620 --> 00:57:03,370
He saved me in more
than one way, though.

773
00:57:04,080 --> 00:57:07,420
Because it was only through meeting him
that I knew what love really was.

774
00:57:12,180 --> 00:57:14,340
That's quite the story you've cooked up.

775
00:57:15,050 --> 00:57:16,720
It's like something out of a novel.

776
00:57:17,970 --> 00:57:20,770
You don't believe me?

777
00:57:22,020 --> 00:57:25,940
I know your real name
is Tsunemi Tsuchida.

778
00:57:27,610 --> 00:57:29,110
And you have a rap sheet.

779
00:57:31,190 --> 00:57:34,610
For theft, shoplifting,

780
00:57:36,280 --> 00:57:37,330
and pros...

781
00:57:37,870 --> 00:57:39,200
Is that what they told you?

782
00:57:39,740 --> 00:57:41,290
Yes, a detective did.

783
00:57:42,540 --> 00:57:45,210
So, you think it was me
who tore the apartment up?

784
00:57:46,170 --> 00:57:47,290
Wasn't it?

785
00:57:48,840 --> 00:57:50,920
Is everything my fault now?

786
00:57:57,300 --> 00:58:04,310
<i>These aren't tears.</i>

787
00:58:06,350 --> 00:58:11,990
<i>ALL this is.</i>

788
00:58:13,320 --> 00:58:20,330
<i>Is where the fickle rain.</i>

789
00:58:20,950 --> 00:58:26,080
<i>Has wet my cheeks a little.</i>

790
00:58:28,000 --> 00:58:35,010
<i>This is Algeria, at the end of the earth.</i>

791
00:58:35,930 --> 00:58:37,590
My dad liked that song.

792
00:58:40,890 --> 00:58:42,390
That's just a coincidence, right?

793
00:58:45,350 --> 00:58:46,850
Right! Just a coincidence!

794
00:58:53,110 --> 00:58:54,150
I'm leaving.

795
00:58:56,070 --> 00:58:57,110
Izumi!

796
00:59:03,540 --> 00:59:06,870
I've fallen in love with someone.

797
00:59:08,000 --> 00:59:10,880
I thought Takashi would be the last,
but here I go again!

798
00:59:11,750 --> 00:59:13,130
Can you forgive me?

799
00:59:15,970 --> 00:59:18,300
Why do you need my blessing?

800
00:59:19,260 --> 00:59:20,850
Because you're Takashi's daughter.

801
00:59:21,600 --> 00:59:24,350
And I promised him I'd take care of you,

802
00:59:24,470 --> 00:59:27,020
but then I went and fell
for someone else.

803
00:59:27,140 --> 00:59:28,440
Mayumi.

804
00:59:29,810 --> 00:59:31,360
