every time you go to bed at night.

863
01:06:44,540 --> 01:06:48,290
Sometimes you want to howl, like a wolf.

864
01:06:51,550 --> 01:06:52,880
You mean that she...

865
01:06:54,130 --> 01:06:55,880
Mayumi is just as rotten?

866
01:06:56,010 --> 01:06:57,050
No.

867
01:07:01,600 --> 01:07:03,640
I don't know!

868
01:07:06,940 --> 01:07:08,230
When I met her,

869
01:07:09,150 --> 01:07:13,190
she told me I looked like her old lover.

870
01:07:14,150 --> 01:07:18,160
"She told me I looked like her old lover."

871
01:07:20,450 --> 01:07:22,990
That he was dead now,
but I reminded her of him.

872
01:07:24,580 --> 01:07:27,410
"That he was dead now,
but I reminded her of him."

873
01:07:30,540 --> 01:07:35,460
I was just a substitute
for the man she loved!

874
01:07:37,090 --> 01:07:41,720
<i>"I was just a substitute
for the man she loved!"</i>

875
01:08:41,450 --> 01:08:42,490
Morning!

876
01:08:42,620 --> 01:08:43,820
- Morning!
- Morning, Boss!

877
01:08:47,120 --> 01:08:48,200
What's today's schedule?

878
01:08:48,330 --> 01:08:50,540
Well, patrolling our territory, as usual,

879
01:08:50,660 --> 01:08:53,540
then in the evening, Mr. Hamaguchi
has invited you for dinner.

880
01:09:00,170 --> 01:09:02,180
As in the boss of
Hamaguchi Enterprises?

881
01:09:02,300 --> 01:09:05,350
Yes. You haven't exchanged sake cups
with him since becoming chairman,

882
01:09:05,470 --> 01:09:06,510
so it's very important.

883
01:09:07,560 --> 01:09:08,850
Exchanged sake cups?

884
01:09:10,100 --> 01:09:12,020
Sounds like a wedding!

885
01:09:12,140 --> 01:09:15,480
Well, it is a wedding of sorts.
Between two yakuza families.

886
01:09:16,270 --> 01:09:17,780
So, where are we having dinner?

887
01:09:17,900 --> 01:09:21,490
At Mr. Hamaguchi's house.
He asked you to come alone, Boss.

888
01:09:22,150 --> 01:09:23,200
Alone?

889
01:09:23,740 --> 01:09:24,910
Are you soft in the head?

890
01:09:26,330 --> 01:09:28,450
I just mean, we shouldn't send
a girl the Boss' age

891
01:09:29,330 --> 01:09:31,080
over there all by herself.

892
01:09:35,750 --> 01:09:37,590
I'm the chairman!

893
01:09:38,960 --> 01:09:41,670
What's age or gender got to do with it?

894
01:09:41,800 --> 01:09:43,380
But, Boss, he's.

895
01:09:44,090 --> 01:09:45,220
I'm going.

896
01:09:45,800 --> 01:09:48,600
The chairman mustn't run away.

897
01:09:48,720 --> 01:09:49,770
But Boss...

898
01:09:50,720 --> 01:09:51,770
The thing is.

899
01:10:00,190 --> 01:10:03,490
I'm glad you enjoyed dinner.

900
01:10:04,490 --> 01:10:07,700
Dishes and dishes of food I'd never
seen before just kept coming!

901
01:10:07,830 --> 01:10:09,700
I feel like I'm going to burst!

902
01:10:10,830 --> 01:10:14,040
This helps with digestion. Try it.

903
01:10:21,380 --> 01:10:22,670
It's delicious!

904
01:10:22,800 --> 01:10:24,760
Really? I'm glad you think so.

905
01:10:26,220 --> 01:10:29,300
That you're so politely
enjoying my hospitality

906
01:10:29,430 --> 01:10:31,680
makes me feel it was worth inviting you.

907
01:10:33,430 --> 01:10:35,310
Now we've had dinner together,

908
01:10:35,440 --> 01:10:37,900
Hamaguchi Enterprises
and the Medaka Family

909
01:10:38,020 --> 01:10:40,020
are properly allied, right?

910
01:10:40,150 --> 01:10:42,740
Well, I'm not so sure of that.

911
01:10:44,570 --> 01:10:49,320
We've yet to make this official,
chairman to chairman, I think.

912
01:10:50,080 --> 01:10:51,120
Huh?

913
01:10:52,370 --> 01:10:55,080
Now, let's go, shall we?

914
01:10:55,210 --> 01:10:56,540
Yeah?

915
01:10:56,670 --> 01:10:57,750
Go where?

916
01:10:58,830 --> 01:10:59,880
Well...

917
01:11:01,170 --> 01:11:02,210
Come on.

918
01:11:03,090 --> 01:11:04,760
- Stand up.
- No, thank you.

919
01:11:04,880 --> 01:11:07,180
- Let's go.
- I wasn't planning on staying the night.

920
01:11:07,300 --> 01:11:09,930
Besides, I don't have
my pajamas with me...

921
01:11:10,050 --> 01:11:12,260
Come on. Don't worry
about your pajamas.

922
01:11:12,390 --> 01:11:14,220
You can sleep naked.

923
01:11:17,850 --> 01:11:19,650
Excellent!

924
01:11:19,770 --> 01:11:21,650
So you are a virgin!

925
01:11:23,980 --> 01:11:25,860
That's just perfect.

926
01:11:25,990 --> 01:11:29,070
That means we can make
a proper alliance.

927
01:11:36,160 --> 01:11:38,460
Come along. That's a good girl.

928
01:11:38,580 --> 01:11:39,920
Let's go, shall we?

929
01:11:40,040 --> 01:11:42,000
Okay? Come on, let's go.

930
01:11:42,130 --> 01:11:43,170
Hey, now!

931
01:11:43,300 --> 01:11:44,760
Come with me.

932
01:11:45,210 --> 01:11:46,260
Hey!

933
01:11:46,840 --> 01:11:48,590
Alright, let's go up now.

934
01:11:48,720 --> 01:11:49,760
No!

935
01:11:50,300 --> 01:11:52,470
That's it, on your feet now.

936
01:11:53,310 --> 01:11:54,430
Okay, okay!

937
01:11:54,560 --> 01:11:55,970
Oh, you're a feisty one!

938
01:11:56,640 --> 01:11:58,020
What fun.

939
01:11:58,140 --> 01:11:59,560
Up you go.

940
01:11:59,690 --> 01:12:02,060
Keep going! Keep going!

941
01:12:13,080 --> 01:12:14,370
Mr. Hamaguchi?

942
01:12:14,490 --> 01:12:15,540
What?

943
01:12:16,080 --> 01:12:17,870
A visitor.

944
01:12:18,000 --> 01:12:19,710
I can't see them right now, I'm busy!

945
01:12:20,330 --> 01:12:22,210
She calls herself Mayumi.

946
01:12:22,670 --> 01:12:24,000
Mayumi Sandaiji.

947
01:12:24,750 --> 01:12:27,300
She said to tell you
that she's Fatso's daughter.

948
01:12:27,420 --> 01:12:28,470
What?

949
01:12:30,510 --> 01:12:31,640
Just as I thought!

950
01:12:33,680 --> 01:12:34,720
Get out, now!

951
01:12:34,850 --> 01:12:37,350
- Mayumi!
- Sakuma's waiting for you outside.

952
01:12:38,100 --> 01:12:39,270
What about you, Mayumi?

953
01:12:39,770 --> 01:12:42,480
You're not going to let the both of us go,
are you, Mr. Hamaguchi?

954
01:12:45,730 --> 01:12:47,820
If I'm going to let go
of a fresh young virgin,

955
01:12:49,110 --> 01:12:51,990
I'm going to need
some serious compensation.

956
01:12:53,570 --> 01:12:55,580
This is the kind of man
you're dealing with.

957
01:12:55,700 --> 01:12:56,950
Do you see now?

958
01:12:57,080 --> 01:12:58,580
Be more careful from now on.

959
01:13:01,960 --> 01:13:03,000
I'm sorry.

960
01:13:04,330 --> 01:13:05,380
Go.

961
01:13:06,460 --> 01:13:08,380
He's worried sick.

962
01:13:11,760 --> 01:13:13,340
Sakuma is?

963
01:13:14,090 --> 01:13:15,930
He's waiting outside

964
01:13:16,390 --> 01:13:20,730
so he could come in and kill Hamaguchi
if he did anything to you!

965
01:13:22,900 --> 01:13:24,150
He's such a fool.

966
01:13:24,270 --> 01:13:26,110
A yakuza down to his very bones.

967
01:13:27,820 --> 01:13:29,900
Go to him. Now!

968
01:13:32,200 --> 01:13:36,280
My, my! This is one for the books!
The Sandaiji girl!

969
01:13:37,620 --> 01:13:40,700
Who'd have thought the woman
I could never talk into bed

970
01:13:40,830 --> 01:13:42,870
would end up coming running to me!

971
01:13:43,830 --> 01:13:47,630
Just what does that virgin girl
mean to you?

972
01:13:48,460 --> 01:13:51,130
I guess you could call it my duty.
I made someone a promise.

973
01:13:51,720 --> 01:13:55,470
I can't let monsters like you hurt her.

974
01:13:56,050 --> 01:13:58,100
That's all our relationship is.

975
01:13:59,890 --> 01:14:00,930
Boss!

976
01:14:02,310 --> 01:14:03,350
Boss!

977
01:14:04,850 --> 01:14:06,020
Boss!

978
01:14:06,150 --> 01:14:07,440
Are you alright?

979
01:14:07,560 --> 01:14:08,610
Boss?

980
01:14:09,360 --> 01:14:11,030
Boss! You're not hurt, right?

981
01:14:11,570 --> 01:14:12,610
Boss!

982
01:14:14,660 --> 01:14:15,910
Thank goodness.

983
01:14:16,030 --> 01:14:17,070
Thank goodness.

984
01:14:33,670 --> 01:14:34,880
I'm sorry.

985
01:14:36,890 --> 01:14:37,930
Mayumi...

986
01:14:39,510 --> 01:14:41,350
She sacrificed herself for me...

987
01:14:41,470 --> 01:14:44,430
It's okay. It was her own decision.

988
01:14:49,730 --> 01:14:51,940
Is it really, though?

989
01:14:55,030 --> 01:14:56,070
Is that how men,

990
01:14:57,530 --> 01:14:58,570
and women

991
01:15:00,490 --> 01:15:01,790
are?

992
01:15:05,410 --> 01:15:06,500
It's over now.

993
01:15:08,290 --> 01:15:11,460
You're done dealing with him.

994
01:15:50,920 --> 01:15:52,250
Coffee's ready.

995
01:16:22,320 --> 01:16:23,490
Morning!

996
01:16:23,620 --> 01:16:24,830
Good morning, Boss!

997
01:16:24,950 --> 01:16:26,160
Good morning.

998
01:16:26,290 --> 01:16:27,370
Boss,

999
01:16:28,160 --> 01:16:30,290
shouldn't you rest up at home
a little longer?

1000
01:16:31,170 --> 01:16:32,380
I'm fine.

1001
01:16:33,460 --> 01:16:34,500
Are you sure?

1002
01:16:38,380 --> 01:16:39,930
Oh, this is for you.

1003
01:16:45,560 --> 01:16:46,600
What is it?

1004
01:16:56,900 --> 01:16:57,940
Boss!

1005
01:16:59,650 --> 01:17:01,860
The rice fish is cute, isn't he?

1006
01:17:03,030 --> 01:17:04,620
- This one?
- No, over here.

1007
01:17:05,620 --> 01:17:06,660
- This one?
- Yeah.

1008
01:17:07,910 --> 01:17:09,500
And over to the right...

1009
01:17:09,620 --> 01:17:11,620
That's it. A bit more Yeah...

1010
01:17:12,580 --> 01:17:13,630
His name's Taro.

1011
01:17:15,130 --> 01:17:16,170
Good morning.

1012
01:17:16,290 --> 01:17:18,550
You see the little guy beneath him?
That's the one.

1013
01:17:19,090 --> 01:17:20,630
He doesn't move much, does he?

1014
01:17:21,630 --> 01:17:24,090
- I wonder if something's wrong with him.
- Maybe.

1015
01:17:25,470 --> 01:17:26,680
The most energetic one...

1016
01:17:27,890 --> 01:17:30,600
A bit lower. More. Lower. Lower.

1017
01:17:31,350 --> 01:17:33,270
There! He's the liveliest.

1018
01:17:33,400 --> 01:17:34,770
I'm being tailed.

1019
01:17:34,900 --> 01:17:35,940
- What?
- Huh?

1020
01:17:36,060 --> 01:17:40,150
I've felt like someone's
been following me all morning.

1021
01:17:40,780 --> 01:17:41,860
Following you?

1022
01:17:43,360 --> 01:17:44,450
It's freaking me out.

1023
01:17:57,130 --> 01:17:58,300
Detective?

1024
01:18:00,010 --> 01:18:01,170
I knew it was you!

1025
01:18:01,300 --> 01:18:05,260
You had a chat with the boss
in that underground cafe, didn't you?

1026
01:18:05,840 --> 01:18:07,350
I saw you.

1027
01:18:08,260 --> 01:18:09,600
Who the hell are you?

1028
01:18:10,430 --> 01:18:12,600
I'm Mei, from the Medaka Family.

1029
01:18:13,310 --> 01:18:16,440
I'm the boss' bodyguard.
Good to meet you.

1030
01:18:17,730 --> 01:18:20,110
Do you have something
to discuss with the boss?

1031
01:18:20,780 --> 01:18:24,070
Did you find Hiko's killer?

1032
01:18:25,360 --> 01:18:29,410
Sorry, but that case is a dead end.

1033
01:18:29,950 --> 01:18:31,830
There are no leads whatsoever.

1034
01:18:31,950 --> 01:18:34,750
So what do you want
with the boss, then?

1035
01:18:36,580 --> 01:18:37,670
What's this?

1036
01:18:38,460 --> 01:18:41,000
Are you interrogating me?

1037
01:18:41,760 --> 01:18:44,130
I'm the detective here!

1038
01:18:45,130 --> 01:18:48,760
Sakuma told me not to let
anyone suspicious go inside.

1039
01:18:48,890 --> 01:18:50,140
Suspicious?

1040
01:18:50,930 --> 01:18:52,890
What's suspicious about me? Huh?

1041
01:19:00,360 --> 01:19:02,480
What's so suspicious about me?

1042
01:19:03,530 --> 01:19:04,570
Tell me.

1043
01:19:05,990 --> 01:19:08,660
What is it?

1044
01:19:10,870 --> 01:19:12,830
Aren't you meant to be a cop?

1045
01:19:13,870 --> 01:19:16,210
Is this how you protect your boss?

1046
01:19:17,000 --> 01:19:18,210
What a joke.

1047
01:19:18,750 --> 01:19:21,710
It's my business what I want with her.

1048
01:19:22,880 --> 01:19:24,300
I need to speak with her.

1049
01:19:25,420 --> 01:19:27,760
In person.

1050
01:19:29,760 --> 01:19:31,180
You got a problem with that?

1051
01:19:31,810 --> 01:19:32,930
Punk!

1052
01:19:33,060 --> 01:19:34,220
Speak up!

1053
01:19:37,480 --> 01:19:38,520
Sorry.

1054
01:19:38,650 --> 01:19:42,770
I'm in a bad mood today!

1055
01:19:45,570 --> 01:19:47,280
And I'm feeling pretty impatient.

1056
01:19:49,490 --> 01:19:50,570
Wait!

1057
01:19:58,290 --> 01:19:59,960
You're not seeing the boss.

1058
01:20:02,000 --> 01:20:05,920
There's no way I'd let
a son of a bitch like you up there!

1059
01:20:09,380 --> 01:20:11,390
Not to see our chairman!

1060
01:20:18,520 --> 01:20:19,560
You want to die?

1061
01:20:20,190 --> 01:20:21,230
Don't struggle.

1062
01:20:22,020 --> 01:20:23,480
Don't move, or you're dead.

1063
01:20:31,570 --> 01:20:32,700
Fine.

1064
01:20:35,040 --> 01:20:38,540
I'll arrange to see your boss
another time.

1065
01:21:00,770 --> 01:21:02,060
No...

1066
01:21:03,610 --> 01:21:06,440
Something bad's going to happen, Boss!

1067
01:21:09,240 --> 01:21:10,860
Did you get into another fight?

1068
01:21:13,950 --> 01:21:15,370
Who did this to you?

1069
01:21:19,750 --> 01:21:21,000
This is bad...

1070
01:21:21,580 --> 01:21:22,790
You must be in pain!

1071
01:21:22,920 --> 01:21:24,040
It's bad...

1072
01:21:27,670 --> 01:21:30,470
You know a cop called Kuroki, right?

1073
01:21:30,590 --> 01:21:31,720
Mr. Kuroki?

1074
01:21:32,180 --> 01:21:33,390
You know him well?

1075
01:21:34,180 --> 01:21:35,510
Not really...

1076
01:21:36,720 --> 01:21:40,140
He seems like a good person, so...

1077
01:21:42,940 --> 01:21:44,850
- Shall I take you to the hospital?
- No.

1078
01:21:44,980 --> 01:21:46,360
This is nothing!

1079
01:21:46,980 --> 01:21:48,230
I'll be fine in a few days.

1080
01:21:48,360 --> 01:21:49,570
- Take your shirt off.
- Huh?

1081
01:22:04,460 --> 01:22:05,540
Come on!

1082
01:22:08,170 --> 01:22:09,460
It looks terrible!

1083
01:22:14,260 --> 01:22:15,840
Stay still, okay?

1084
01:22:19,310 --> 01:22:20,430
Does it hurt?

1085
01:22:22,390 --> 01:22:23,520
It feels good!

1086
01:22:26,440 --> 01:22:27,650
Don't move.

1087
01:22:37,660 --> 01:22:39,160
Press here a second.

1088
01:22:40,910 --> 01:22:41,950
That's it.

1089
01:22:59,760 --> 01:23:02,100
It's fine, I can do it myself.

1090
01:23:02,220 --> 01:23:03,770
Stay put!

1091
01:23:03,890 --> 01:23:06,190
You'll open the wound
if you move around. Right?

1092
01:23:08,060 --> 01:23:09,480
Put your hands on your head.

1093
01:23:18,240 --> 01:23:19,450
- Does it hurt?
- No.

1094
01:23:23,870 --> 01:23:25,910
You smell good, Boss!

1095
01:23:27,540 --> 01:23:29,210
I'm not wearing any perfume.

1096
01:23:29,330 --> 01:23:32,800
Really? You kind of smell like my mom.

1097
01:23:34,760 --> 01:23:37,590
Am I like your mom?

1098
01:23:37,720 --> 01:23:43,100
No! She's a drunk and a whore.

1099
01:23:46,940 --> 01:23:49,730
Sorry, I'm babbling.

1100
01:23:49,850 --> 01:23:51,730
I can do the rest.

1101
01:23:51,860 --> 01:23:54,690
Maybe I'll be like that when I grow up.

1102
01:23:56,190 --> 01:23:58,450
You're kind, aren't you, Boss?

1103
01:24:29,560 --> 01:24:31,350
You smell so nice.

1104
01:24:33,860 --> 01:24:35,360
Like my mom.

1105
01:24:40,070 --> 01:24:41,570
You smell like Mom.

1106
01:24:49,460 --> 01:24:50,620
It's nice.

1107
01:25:18,030 --> 01:25:20,860
I'm sorry! That was inexcusable, Boss!

1108
01:25:21,400 --> 01:25:23,700
I'm sorry! I'm sorry!

1109
01:25:37,300 --> 01:25:38,460
Who are you?

1110
01:25:40,470 --> 01:25:41,510
Mei!

1111
01:25:46,890 --> 01:25:48,350
Kindly come with us, would you?

1112
01:25:57,860 --> 01:25:59,530
Why did you kill him?

1113
01:25:59,650 --> 01:26:01,360
Why did you have to shoot him?

1114
01:28:21,920 --> 01:28:23,000
Have a seat.

1115
01:28:28,300 --> 01:28:30,220
What a beautiful young lady you are.

1116
01:28:31,220 --> 01:28:34,760
I particularly like
that sparkle in your eyes.

1117
01:28:35,890 --> 01:28:37,060
I had

1118
01:28:38,890 --> 01:28:42,860
a daughter with beautiful eyes
just like yours.

1119
01:29:04,750 --> 01:29:07,630
That was a long time ago, though.

1120
01:29:23,980 --> 01:29:25,770
What did you do with the package?

1121
01:29:29,360 --> 01:29:30,400
The heroin.

1122
01:29:32,570 --> 01:29:34,320
I've never even seen it!

1123
01:29:36,660 --> 01:29:39,910
You see, it was meant for me.

1124
01:29:41,500 --> 01:29:43,670
But there was a little mishap

1125
01:29:44,750 --> 01:29:46,880
and it ended up with you.

1126
01:29:52,590 --> 01:29:54,180
I want you to give it back to me.

1127
01:29:56,800 --> 01:29:58,970
I can't give back what I don't have!

1128
01:30:27,000 --> 01:30:28,170
Listen to me.

1129
01:30:28,840 --> 01:30:31,840
Only God has the right to decide
who lives and dies.

1130
01:30:32,470 --> 01:30:35,220
But He's busy elsewhere right now.

1131
01:30:36,260 --> 01:30:37,850
So, here in Japan,

1132
01:30:38,800 --> 01:30:41,520
we're acting on His behalf.

1133
01:30:57,870 --> 01:31:01,160
I'll tell you how I lost my legs.

1134
01:31:03,410 --> 01:31:04,830
I tried to kill myself.

1135
01:31:07,670 --> 01:31:10,340
I rigged a landmine up on the floor

1136
01:31:11,130 --> 01:31:13,170
and slowly stepped on it.

1137
01:31:13,300 --> 01:31:18,390
The thing is, just stepping on a landmine
won't detonate it.

1138
01:31:20,300 --> 01:31:22,470
But if you were to shift your weight

1139
01:31:22,600 --> 01:31:26,350
as you were standing on it
even just a little bit...

1140
01:31:27,940 --> 01:31:31,020
Boom! It would be triggered instantly.

1141
01:31:32,400 --> 01:31:35,650
So if you want to live,

1142
01:31:36,280 --> 01:31:40,830
you can't move a muscle.

1143
01:31:44,120 --> 01:31:49,420
I stood there for three days.

1144
01:31:51,090 --> 01:31:56,760
First my feet went numb, and then
the numbness spread to my whole body.

1145
01:32:01,140 --> 01:32:04,100
That feeling How can I explain it?

1146
01:32:04,220 --> 01:32:09,940
Yes, the fear of death mingled
with the shuddering of my body...

1147
01:32:10,400 --> 01:32:12,940
It was pleasure!

1148
01:32:15,070 --> 01:32:17,190
I wonder if you can understand

1149
01:32:17,320 --> 01:32:22,200
how pleasure can come
from being so close to death.

1150
01:32:22,320 --> 01:32:25,040
I can't! And I don't want to!

1151
01:32:25,620 --> 01:32:27,660
Let me help you.

1152
01:32:29,710 --> 01:32:31,040
Where's the heroin?

1153
01:32:43,970 --> 01:32:51,970
<i>These aren't tears.</i>

1154
01:32:53,190 --> 01:33:00,490
<i>ALL this is.</i>

1155
01:33:00,610 --> 01:33:07,950
<i>Is where the fickle rain.</i>

1156
01:33:08,540 --> 01:33:14,710
<i>Has wet my cheeks a little.</i>

1157
01:33:14,840 --> 01:33:18,800
<i>This is Algeria</i>

1158
01:33:18,920 --> 01:33:20,130
I need your help!

1159
01:33:21,300 --> 01:33:24,300
Our chairman has been kidnapped
by Fatso.

1160
01:33:25,970 --> 01:33:30,810
They'll only spare her life
if we come up with the heroin.

1161
01:33:31,560 --> 01:33:33,440
But Fatso's got it wrong.

1162
01:33:33,560 --> 01:33:35,310
We don't have any damn heroin.

1163
01:33:36,320 --> 01:33:38,860
Right! You wouldn't touch that stuff.

1164
01:33:40,070 --> 01:33:42,070
Please...

1165
01:33:42,740 --> 01:33:46,280
Cut to the chase. You need me
because I'm Fatso's daughter, right?

1166
01:33:49,200 --> 01:33:50,540
I'm begging you.

1167
01:33:52,460 --> 01:33:55,250
Please tell me where your father is.

1168
01:33:56,210 --> 01:33:57,920
What will you do if I tell you?

1169
01:33:58,050 --> 01:34:00,420
I'll go see him.

1170
01:34:00,920 --> 01:34:03,470
We'll talk it over.

1171
01:34:04,260 --> 01:34:06,300
And what about when he
doesn't believe you?

1172
01:34:09,810 --> 01:34:13,690
You should know that talking to Fatso
isn't going to solve anything.

1173
01:34:15,350 --> 01:34:16,650
In that case...

1174
01:34:16,770 --> 01:34:18,730
He'll kill you.

1175
01:34:28,990 --> 01:34:30,580
Forget it.

1176
01:34:32,500 --> 01:34:34,580
It's suicide.

1177
01:34:37,000 --> 01:34:38,500
Don't move!

1178
01:34:40,880 --> 01:34:42,420
It's too dangerous.

1179
01:34:44,260 --> 01:34:46,970
You're in grave danger.

1180
01:34:49,930 --> 01:34:52,640
That landmine is highly sensitive.

1181
01:34:54,060 --> 01:34:56,350
If you move your body

1182
01:34:56,940 --> 01:35:00,320
or your center of gravity
shifts even a little,

1183
01:35:01,980 --> 01:35:04,110
you'll be blown to pieces in an instant.

1184
01:35:06,910 --> 01:35:08,410
Mr. Fatso?

1185
01:35:10,200 --> 01:35:12,790
I can't hear her. Turn up the volume.

1186
01:35:14,040 --> 01:35:15,120
What was that?

1187
01:35:17,250 --> 01:35:19,630
You need to see a psychiatrist.

1188
01:35:21,590 --> 01:35:24,300
You demand heroin
that I don't even have.

1189
01:35:25,010 --> 01:35:27,680
You enjoy watching people suffer.

1190
01:35:29,300 --> 01:35:30,970
You're sick.

1191
01:35:32,470 --> 01:35:33,520
Very well.

1192
01:35:34,230 --> 01:35:39,400
I'll tell you why
I'm so interested in the heroin.

1193
01:35:41,270 --> 01:35:42,820
You see,

1194
01:35:44,070 --> 01:35:47,860
it's not just about the money.

1195
01:35:50,910 --> 01:35:54,370
I want the number
of heroin addicts in Japan

1196
01:35:54,500 --> 01:35:57,500
to grow by thousands, millions, even.

1197
01:35:58,870 --> 01:36:01,710
Then, when they come off the heroin
and get withdrawal symptoms,

1198
01:36:02,630 --> 01:36:04,670
I'll sit back and watch

1199
01:36:05,510 --> 01:36:10,640
as they writhe about in agony.

1200
01:36:13,310 --> 01:36:14,430
You're the Devil!

1201
01:36:16,100 --> 01:36:17,350
Thank you.

1202
01:36:18,140 --> 01:36:22,400
That's the greatest compliment
you could pay me.

1203
01:36:28,450 --> 01:36:29,570
Mayumi!

1204
01:36:35,290 --> 01:36:37,580
Stay back! It will explode!

1205
01:36:38,830 --> 01:36:40,620
I can't take any more!

1206
01:36:44,750 --> 01:36:45,800
Dad!

1207
01:36:46,300 --> 01:36:47,380
Mayumi!

1208
01:36:53,600 --> 01:36:54,680
Stay back!

1209
01:37:04,320 --> 01:37:06,940
Dad! Turn it off!

1210
01:37:09,450 --> 01:37:11,700
I'll tell you where the heroin is!

1211
01:37:12,320 --> 01:37:13,570
Turn it off!

1212
01:37:20,710 --> 01:37:25,920
I'm sorry. I tried to shut you out.

1213
01:37:27,300 --> 01:37:29,090
Not because of you,

1214
01:37:29,210 --> 01:37:32,220
more just what you represented,
I suppose.

1215
01:37:33,470 --> 01:37:35,890
Well, it was only through
living with you, Izumi,

1216
01:37:36,010 --> 01:37:39,020
that I came to start examining
my own shortcomings.

1217
01:37:40,770 --> 01:37:41,810
Izumi.

1218
01:37:43,650 --> 01:37:46,020
I don't like to be left out.

1219
01:37:47,020 --> 01:37:48,780
Now, Mayumi.

1220
01:37:48,900 --> 01:37:51,990
Isn't it about time you shared with me
where the heroin's stashed?

1221
01:37:52,650 --> 01:37:55,740
If you don't, the girl
will be going back to...

1222
01:37:55,870 --> 01:37:57,450
It's in her apartment.

1223
01:37:57,580 --> 01:37:59,660
What? That makes no sense.

1224
01:37:59,790 --> 01:38:02,160
I had that place searched exhaustively...

1225
01:38:02,290 --> 01:38:06,210
You were searching for the wrong thing.
You were looking for powder, right?

1226
01:38:06,880 --> 01:38:10,630
I dissolved it in water and put it
in bottles of lotion.

1227
01:38:11,720 --> 01:38:14,890
That's my girl!

1228
01:38:17,600 --> 01:38:19,640
- Hey, Kuroki!
- Yes, sir?

1229
01:38:22,140 --> 01:38:24,020
Did you hear that just now?

1230
01:38:26,110 --> 01:38:27,150
Mr. Kuroki?

1231
01:38:27,690 --> 01:38:30,110
I didn't want to see you here like this.

1232
01:38:30,230 --> 01:38:33,490
This cop sold his soul to the Devil.

1233
01:38:33,610 --> 01:38:35,700
He'll do anything for money.

1234
01:38:36,160 --> 01:38:40,330
Absolutely. It was me who tortured
and killed that punk Hiko.

1235
01:38:41,500 --> 01:38:42,540
Why?

1236
01:38:43,160 --> 01:38:45,080
We couldn't find the heroin
in your apartment.

1237
01:38:45,210 --> 01:38:46,960
So we worked on your men.

1238
01:38:48,000 --> 01:38:49,710
You didn't have to kill him!

1239
01:38:49,840 --> 01:38:52,050
He'd seen my face. I had no choice.

1240
01:38:52,170 --> 01:38:53,220
Hey, Kuroki!

1241
01:38:54,300 --> 01:39:00,470
Sit down and tell the young lady
the whole story.

1242
01:39:01,270 --> 01:39:02,520
Gladly.

1243
01:39:04,310 --> 01:39:07,810
Security was unusually tight
at Narita Airport that day.

1244
01:39:08,310 --> 01:39:10,360
That was how it began.

1245
01:39:11,280 --> 01:39:16,280
I knew that the narcotics officers were
onto me after I picked up the heroin.

1246
01:39:17,280 --> 01:39:19,950
I was questioned for 30 minutes
before being released.

1247
01:39:20,080 --> 01:39:23,250
While I was being questioned,
Takashi Hoshi crashed into the truck.

1248
01:39:23,700 --> 01:39:26,960
Takashi found a suspicious package
in his bag,

1249
01:39:27,080 --> 01:39:29,590
so he gave it to me
when I came to see him at the airport.

1250
01:39:29,710 --> 01:39:31,880
It was a real shock
when I went to your apartment.

1251
01:39:32,000 --> 01:39:35,090
Who should answer the door
but my boss' daughter?

1252
01:39:35,720 --> 01:39:39,720
This moron said I was in the way,
and that I had to leave.

1253
01:39:40,300 --> 01:39:43,220
He said he'd arrest me and hand me
over to Fatso if I disobeyed him.

1254
01:39:45,020 --> 01:39:47,690
So that's why you vanished so suddenly?

1255
01:39:50,020 --> 01:39:52,730
I never expected
things to turn out like this.

1256
01:39:52,860 --> 01:39:55,820
Who would have thought
that a single package of heroin

1257
01:39:55,940 --> 01:39:58,780
could lead to such a tragedy?

1258
01:40:01,070 --> 01:40:05,290
You completely fooled me
with that lotion bottle trick, though.

1259
01:40:05,410 --> 01:40:06,620
I better get going, then.

1260
01:40:07,160 --> 01:40:10,040
I won't feel at ease
until I find the heroin.

1261
01:40:19,510 --> 01:40:23,600
Let's enjoy our meal until Kuroki
returns with the heroin, shall we?

1262
01:40:24,850 --> 01:40:28,600
This is the world's finest delicacy.

1263
01:40:28,730 --> 01:40:30,730
It's not every day you get to eat it.

1264
01:40:48,960 --> 01:40:50,500
What a sublime taste.

1265
01:41:03,100 --> 01:41:04,470
<i>Délicieux!</i>

1266
01:41:07,100 --> 01:41:08,140
What is it?

1267
01:41:08,810 --> 01:41:09,850
Brains.

1268
01:41:10,390 --> 01:41:11,480
Huh?

1269
01:41:11,600 --> 01:41:12,810
Monkey brains.

1270
01:41:25,620 --> 01:41:26,660
What's the matter?

1271
01:41:27,580 --> 01:41:28,830
I need to use the bathroom...

1272
01:41:28,950 --> 01:41:30,460
Hey! Show her the way.

1273
01:41:43,140 --> 01:41:44,180
Hold it right there.

1274
01:41:45,300 --> 01:41:46,390
Sakuma!

1275
01:41:47,810 --> 01:41:48,850
Don't look behind you!

1276
01:41:50,480 --> 01:41:51,600
Drop your gun!

1277
01:41:53,020 --> 01:41:57,270
Oh, dear. I didn't want
to fight you, Brother.

1278
01:41:57,900 --> 01:41:59,360
Then drop the gun.

1279
01:42:06,070 --> 01:42:08,580
Please! Please don't kill me!

1280
01:42:09,950 --> 01:42:11,410
Please...

1281
01:42:12,210 --> 01:42:13,620
Don't kill me...

1282
01:42:54,670 --> 01:42:56,040
Boss!

1283
01:43:00,670 --> 01:43:01,710
Run!

1284
01:43:01,840 --> 01:43:02,880
No!

1285
01:43:04,090 --> 01:43:05,130
Run!

1286
01:43:52,470 --> 01:43:53,720
Sakuma!

1287
01:43:56,230 --> 01:43:57,850
This is bad, Boss.

1288
01:43:58,600 --> 01:44:00,150
We fell into their trap.

1289
01:44:04,570 --> 01:44:06,740
I don't mind. I'm glad!

1290
01:44:07,490 --> 01:44:10,370
I thought I'd never see you again!

1291
01:44:11,240 --> 01:44:12,330
Boss...

1292
01:44:13,450 --> 01:44:15,000
You can't die.

1293
01:44:15,620 --> 01:44:19,370
You have a bad habit of thinking
you'll sort everything out by dying.

1294
01:44:20,420 --> 01:44:21,670
You need to get out of it.

1295
01:44:28,220 --> 01:44:29,380
Sakuma!

1296
01:44:44,400 --> 01:44:45,440
Boss!

1297
01:44:45,980 --> 01:44:47,190
You've got guts...

1298
01:44:48,990 --> 01:44:52,570
Lecturing me with our backs
against the wall like this.

1299
01:44:54,030 --> 01:44:55,370
I'm falling for you.

1300
01:45:02,500 --> 01:45:04,540
Give up this futile effort!

1301
01:45:19,980 --> 01:45:22,150
It's time for some more vivisection.

1302
01:45:23,150 --> 01:45:24,860
- Grab them!
- Wait!

1303
01:45:26,070 --> 01:45:28,150
You promised to spare her.

1304
01:45:31,070 --> 01:45:32,200
Mayumi!

1305
01:45:34,700 --> 01:45:36,910
You really are naive, aren't you?

1306
01:45:37,370 --> 01:45:39,540
Hey. Remove my legs.

1307
01:45:41,120 --> 01:45:42,330
Now!

1308
01:45:51,760 --> 01:45:52,970
Dad!

1309
01:45:53,510 --> 01:45:55,680
Now why would I let go

1310
01:45:57,810 --> 01:46:00,390
of such a great specimen?

1311
01:46:03,690 --> 01:46:06,230
Strip her and fasten her
to the operating table.

1312
01:46:28,630 --> 01:46:30,260
The Sandaiji Family is disbanded!

1313
01:46:30,380 --> 01:46:31,420
Get out!

1314
01:46:36,010 --> 01:46:37,260
Mayumi!

1315
01:46:48,230 --> 01:46:49,360
It's strange.

1316
01:46:50,650 --> 01:46:52,530
I feel like this is the first time

1317
01:46:53,650 --> 01:46:55,570
I've ever seen you look so gentle, Dad.

1318
01:47:43,240 --> 01:47:44,620
Hello?

1319
01:47:44,750 --> 01:47:46,620
<i>Hello? Who is this?</i>

1320
01:47:47,790 --> 01:47:48,960
<i>Mr. Kuroki?</i>

1321
01:47:51,670 --> 01:47:53,300
I've been ambushed.

1322
01:47:54,760 --> 01:47:58,340
The Hamaguchis took the heroin.

1323
01:47:58,470 --> 01:47:59,510
<i>Hello?</i>

1324
01:48:00,100 --> 01:48:01,510
<i>Mr. Kuroki?</i>

1325
01:48:01,640 --> 01:48:02,720
<i>Hang in there!</i>

1326
01:48:02,850 --> 01:48:06,430
Hagiwara double-crossed us.

1327
01:48:06,980 --> 01:48:08,440
- The bastard.
<i>- Mr. Kuroki?</i>

1328
01:48:09,060 --> 01:48:11,480
<i>You're hurt, aren't you?</i>

1329
01:48:12,770 --> 01:48:14,190
<i>Stop talking now!</i>

1330
01:48:15,780 --> 01:48:16,820
<i>Mr. Kuroki?</i>

1331
01:48:16,950 --> 01:48:18,070
Izumi...

1332
01:48:19,530 --> 01:48:22,910
You're a good girl.

1333
01:48:29,370 --> 01:48:30,710
I liked you.

1334
01:48:39,010 --> 01:48:40,180
Bye-bye.

1335
01:49:01,160 --> 01:49:02,370
Why?

1336
01:49:04,450 --> 01:49:06,410
Why did so many people have to die

1337
01:49:09,290 --> 01:49:11,580
over a tiny bit of heroin?

1338
01:49:13,080 --> 01:49:14,170
Because of money.

1339
01:49:16,050 --> 01:49:18,300
It's worth hundreds of millions of yen.

1340
01:49:20,090 --> 01:49:22,050
So everyone loses their minds chasing it.

1341
01:49:23,430 --> 01:49:25,060
That damn Hamaguchi...

1342
01:49:26,470 --> 01:49:30,350
He must have all those bottles lined up
in a row right now, laughing his ass off.

1343
01:49:34,360 --> 01:49:36,110
- Sakuma.
- Yes?

1344
01:49:37,150 --> 01:49:38,690
- Masa.
- Yes, Boss?

1345
01:49:40,650 --> 01:49:41,990
Will you come with me?

1346
01:49:42,490 --> 01:49:43,530
Where to?

1347
01:49:45,370 --> 01:49:46,530
To Hamaguchi's offices.

1348
01:49:46,660 --> 01:49:48,830
Hamaguchi's?

1349
01:49:50,460 --> 01:49:52,000
We're going to storm the place.

1350
01:50:27,280 --> 01:50:28,490
What?

1351
01:50:28,620 --> 01:50:29,790
I need to take a leak.

1352
01:50:29,910 --> 01:50:31,330
Idiot! Get off on the next floor.

1353
01:50:31,450 --> 01:50:34,830
No! I'm going to die with you, Brother!

1354
01:50:36,420 --> 01:50:39,750
Oh, I meant to ask you.

1355
01:50:40,300 --> 01:50:43,130
Are you gay?

1356
01:50:44,930 --> 01:50:49,760
I'm in love with him,
but he doesn't care about me!

1357
01:50:49,890 --> 01:50:52,560
He killed someone
in the yakuza war in Osaka.

1358
01:50:53,520 --> 01:50:55,230
I was inside at the time, too.

1359
01:50:55,690 --> 01:50:58,570
We were in the same cell.

1360
01:50:59,070 --> 01:51:03,150
Going to bed and waking up with him
every day, I guess I.

1361
01:51:04,070 --> 01:51:06,240
I fell in love with him.

1362
01:51:06,910 --> 01:51:08,370
You pervert!

1363
01:51:09,530 --> 01:51:12,000
It's very painful, you know,

1364
01:51:12,120 --> 01:51:13,830
unrequited love...

1365
01:51:25,930 --> 01:51:28,760
- We're from the Medaka Family.
- Huh? Medaka?

1366
01:51:29,720 --> 01:51:32,060
- Is the president in?
- Do you have an appointment?

1367
01:51:32,560 --> 01:51:35,480
He won't see you
without an appointment.

1368
01:51:36,440 --> 01:51:39,310
The chairman of the Medaka Family

1369
01:51:39,810 --> 01:51:42,480
wants to see your boss!

1370
01:51:42,610 --> 01:51:43,990
Hurry up.

1371
01:51:44,110 --> 01:51:45,150
- Go!
- Alright!

1372
01:51:48,280 --> 01:51:49,820
I can't stand women.

1373
01:52:05,170 --> 01:52:06,590
What?

1374
01:52:07,800 --> 01:52:09,090
Graves.

1375
01:52:25,150 --> 01:52:28,110
Ah, welcome! Come in, come in!

1376
01:52:28,240 --> 01:52:31,240
Please, sit down! Take a seat!

1377
01:52:32,240 --> 01:52:33,280
Hagiwara!

1378
01:52:35,500 --> 01:52:38,750
First you turn your back on the Medakas
to work for Fatso,

1379
01:52:39,960 --> 01:52:43,090
and now you bring heroin to suck up
to your new boss, Hamaguchi!

1380
01:52:43,670 --> 01:52:46,880
You're what they call a snake!

1381
01:52:48,380 --> 01:52:49,800
Sorry!

1382
01:52:49,930 --> 01:52:52,390
I'm a very driven man.

1383
01:52:52,970 --> 01:52:55,890
But thanks to you,
now I'm an executive here.

1384
01:52:56,020 --> 01:52:57,810
Gentlemen, gentlemen...

1385
01:53:01,600 --> 01:53:03,770
If you'd like,

1386
01:53:05,150 --> 01:53:08,490
you're more than welcome to join
our management team, Izumi.

1387
01:53:11,160 --> 01:53:16,830
After all, you handed me the two things
I wanted most on a silver platter.

1388
01:53:17,580 --> 01:53:20,250
The heroin, and Fatso's head!

1389
01:53:26,670 --> 01:53:31,050
Alright. Alright, alright.

1390
01:53:31,800 --> 01:53:34,140
You'll like this, I promise.

1391
01:53:35,510 --> 01:53:39,850
I'm handing over part of Fatso's territory
to the Medaka Family.

1392
01:53:39,980 --> 01:53:43,690
Okay? Now you Medakas
can reestablish yourselves.

1393
01:53:44,690 --> 01:53:46,190
Isn't that right, Izumi?

1394
01:53:46,900 --> 01:53:48,280
I-zu-mi!

1395
01:53:52,530 --> 01:53:53,780
What's that look for?

1396
01:53:54,740 --> 01:53:57,540
You keep disrespecting me
by calling me by my first name.

1397
01:53:57,660 --> 01:53:59,450
Especially since you're just an old hick.

1398
01:54:00,250 --> 01:54:02,000
"Hick"? "Old"?

1399
01:54:02,460 --> 01:54:05,840
I'm not interested in
some shitty territory.

1400
01:54:06,590 --> 01:54:08,050
What the hell did you say?

1401
01:54:08,500 --> 01:54:12,010
What I want is the heroin.

1402
01:54:12,630 --> 01:54:13,680
What?

1403
01:54:13,800 --> 01:54:15,800
Hand over everything you have.

1404
01:54:17,010 --> 01:54:18,060
Don't move!

1405
01:54:22,560 --> 01:54:23,940
Hands on your head.

1406
01:54:25,230 --> 01:54:26,900
Now! Do it!

1407
01:54:27,020 --> 01:54:29,440
Do you realize what you're doing? Huh?

1408
01:54:30,030 --> 01:54:33,860
You think you can sell all this?

1409
01:54:34,360 --> 01:54:35,410
Not to mention the fact

1410
01:54:36,910 --> 01:54:39,790
that we're not exactly going
to just let this slide.

1411
01:55:23,960 --> 01:55:25,580
How pleasant!

1412
01:56:04,040 --> 01:56:05,080
Stay right there!

1413
01:56:07,210 --> 01:56:08,500
- Brother...
- Boss!

1414
01:56:09,710 --> 01:56:10,920
Nobody moves!

1415
01:56:11,500 --> 01:56:12,550
Brother!

1416
01:56:14,090 --> 01:56:15,510
Hold me!

1417
01:56:15,630 --> 01:56:16,760
Hold me tight!

1418
01:56:21,970 --> 01:56:23,220
This is nice!

1419
01:56:24,060 --> 01:56:25,600
- Masa!
- Masa!

1420
01:56:31,690 --> 01:56:33,020
I'm so happy.

1421
01:56:35,820 --> 01:56:39,570
I'm with my two favorite people,
and I'm in your arms.

1422
01:56:41,200 --> 01:56:42,450
I can...

1423
01:56:43,580 --> 01:56:44,620
Masa!

1424
01:56:46,330 --> 01:56:47,370
Masa!

1425
01:56:56,090 --> 01:56:57,340
Go to hell!

1426
01:57:35,090 --> 01:57:38,090
WELCOME!

1427
01:57:48,850 --> 01:57:49,890
Boss.

1428
01:57:52,310 --> 01:57:53,480
Everyone's waiting.

1429
01:58:47,780 --> 01:58:48,990
So, it's all over!

1430
01:58:52,410 --> 01:58:54,870
Hiko, Mei, and Masa are all dead.

1431
01:58:56,210 --> 01:58:57,880
This is the end of the Medaka Family.

1432
01:59:02,420 --> 01:59:03,720
I'm sorry.

1433
01:59:05,050 --> 01:59:08,930
I feel like none of this would have
happened if I hadn't become chairman.

1434
01:59:09,640 --> 01:59:10,770
Don't be silly.

1435
01:59:12,810 --> 01:59:14,440
Thanks to you,

1436
01:59:15,690 --> 01:59:18,190
we got to go out in a blaze of glory.

1437
01:59:20,730 --> 01:59:22,280
I have no doubt that these guys

1438
01:59:23,240 --> 01:59:26,070
and the previous chairman
would have heaped praise on you.

1439
01:59:26,570 --> 01:59:27,950
I certainly will.

1440
01:59:28,070 --> 01:59:30,280
Don't, we're not strangers!

1441
01:59:32,290 --> 01:59:33,580
We are now.

1442
01:59:37,380 --> 01:59:39,090
With the family gone,

1443
01:59:40,130 --> 01:59:43,130
you're back to being
the girl in the sailor suit again.

1444
01:59:44,260 --> 01:59:45,380
And I...

1445
01:59:46,680 --> 01:59:49,140
What will you do, Sakuma?

1446
01:59:51,010 --> 01:59:52,430
Leave Tokyo.

1447
01:59:53,720 --> 01:59:55,230
Go out to the country somewhere

1448
01:59:55,350 --> 01:59:57,190
and live a quiet life, I think.

1449
01:59:58,310 --> 02:00:00,860
And what about being a yakuza?

1450
02:00:03,400 --> 02:00:05,650
I'm washing my hands
of the whole bloody business.

1451
02:00:07,360 --> 02:00:08,530
Really?

1452
02:00:10,280 --> 02:00:12,620
The yakuza are going backwards.

1453
02:00:14,790 --> 02:00:17,000
They like to talk about
codes of honor and manhood.

1454
02:00:18,460 --> 02:00:19,630
But deep down,

1455
02:00:20,380 --> 02:00:22,090
they're afraid to move forward.

1456
02:00:23,380 --> 02:00:25,630
So they don't dare to look to the future.

1457
02:00:27,010 --> 02:00:28,840
The yakuza are a bunch
of cowards, really.

1458
02:00:32,300 --> 02:00:33,510
You know who showed me that?

1459
02:00:36,480 --> 02:00:38,060
You did, Boss.

1460
02:00:40,270 --> 02:00:41,650
Don't call me that.

1461
02:00:41,770 --> 02:00:43,730
The Medaka Family
doesn't exist anymore.

1462
02:00:46,400 --> 02:00:47,900
In that case, Miss Hoshi...

1463
02:00:48,030 --> 02:00:49,070
Look after yourself.

1464
02:00:49,610 --> 02:00:50,660
You too, Sakuma.

1465
02:01:18,930 --> 02:01:19,980
Promise me.

1466
02:01:20,690 --> 02:01:22,310
Promise me you'll become a civilian.

1467
02:01:26,110 --> 02:01:27,570
I'll become a civilian.

1468
02:01:28,440 --> 02:01:30,820
Then I'll come visit you
at your apartment sometime.

1469
02:01:35,080 --> 02:01:36,240
I promise you, Boss.

1470
02:01:36,700 --> 02:01:38,120
You did it again!

1471
02:01:49,420 --> 02:01:51,510
- Heave...
- Ho!

1472
02:01:52,720 --> 02:01:54,350
Heave ho!

1473
02:02:03,650 --> 02:02:09,610
SEVERAL MONTHS LATER

1474
02:02:10,530 --> 02:02:11,570
Oh, yeah.

1475
02:02:11,700 --> 02:02:14,870
What happened to
that weird Mayumi person?

1476
02:02:15,370 --> 02:02:16,780
She went to America.

1477
02:02:16,910 --> 02:02:18,040
- America?
- Yeah.

1478
02:02:18,790 --> 02:02:19,910
Good for her.

1479
02:02:20,040 --> 02:02:22,290
She's probably living by herself
in New York.

1480
02:02:22,410 --> 02:02:25,750
Actually, I bet she's got loads
of blond-haired lovers.

1481
02:02:25,880 --> 02:02:28,000
You have it easy
in that department yourself.

1482
02:02:28,710 --> 02:02:29,760
How do you mean?

1483
02:02:29,880 --> 02:02:33,930
Well, you have your pick of at least
three boyfriends whenever you want.

1484
02:02:34,050 --> 02:02:36,850
- Right!
- And would that mean you three?

1485
02:02:36,970 --> 02:02:40,680
- Of course!
- Who else?

1486
02:02:43,600 --> 02:02:44,940
She's laughing!

1487
02:02:45,060 --> 02:02:46,810
Well, I'm glad you're so amused.

1488
02:02:47,310 --> 02:02:50,110
Are we a joke to you?

1489
02:02:50,230 --> 02:02:51,570
No, it's not that!

1490
02:02:51,690 --> 02:02:54,200
It's just been so long since I've heard
you goofing around,

1491
02:02:54,320 --> 02:02:56,120
and I feel all giddy!

1492
02:02:56,240 --> 02:02:58,330
I just can't stop laughing!

1493
02:02:59,370 --> 02:03:00,950
We weren't kidding!

1494
02:03:08,630 --> 02:03:10,000
Excuse me!

1495
02:03:10,130 --> 02:03:12,130
Are you Izumi Hoshi?

1496
02:03:14,630 --> 02:03:16,010
Do you have a moment?

1497
02:03:16,140 --> 02:03:17,220
Yes?

1498
02:03:17,340 --> 02:03:18,390
Not you.

1499
02:03:21,020 --> 02:03:23,180
I'm a police officer.

1500
02:03:25,020 --> 02:03:27,610
Izumi? Are you back to your old tricks?

1501
02:03:47,710 --> 02:03:51,460
There was a fight between
two yakuza late last night.

1502
02:03:57,220 --> 02:03:58,720
- Yakuza?
- Yes.

1503
02:03:59,300 --> 02:04:01,810
He stepped in to break it up, apparently.

1504
02:04:02,390 --> 02:04:05,060
Then one of the gangsters pulled a knife

1505
02:04:05,180 --> 02:04:06,520
and stabbed him in the chest.

1506
02:04:07,020 --> 02:04:08,730
Death would have been almost instant.

1507
02:04:13,980 --> 02:04:16,860
Is he a yakuza, too?

1508
02:04:17,320 --> 02:04:18,490
No, no.

1509
02:04:18,610 --> 02:04:21,200
He's here on business from Hokkaido.

1510
02:04:22,700 --> 02:04:24,580
- Hokkaido?
- Yes.

1511
02:04:25,450 --> 02:04:26,750
One second.

1512
02:04:37,420 --> 02:04:39,430
Please take a look at this.

1513
02:04:41,760 --> 02:04:46,230
I think he was just going to leave his
card in your mailbox or something,

1514
02:04:46,810 --> 02:04:48,270
but he must have changed his mind.

1515
02:04:49,190 --> 02:04:51,650
He decided to come back
to visit you later,

1516
02:04:51,770 --> 02:04:54,190
so he went to kill some time.

1517
02:04:54,320 --> 02:04:56,650
But then he saw the yakuza brawl...

1518
02:04:56,780 --> 02:04:58,070
- Please, stop.
- Huh?

1519
02:05:01,030 --> 02:05:06,750
When he saw them fighting, he couldn't
just stand back and do nothing.

1520
02:05:10,710 --> 02:05:12,000
Because if he did,

1521
02:05:13,880 --> 02:05:16,340
one of them would be hurt over nothing.

1522
02:05:21,470 --> 02:05:22,640
Knowing that,

1523
02:05:24,560 --> 02:05:26,350
he couldn't turn a blind eye.

1524
02:05:27,980 --> 02:05:29,180
If you don't mind my asking,

1525
02:05:29,310 --> 02:05:31,020
what's your relationship
to the deceased?

1526
02:05:31,150 --> 02:05:32,650
MAKOTO SAKUMA HOKKO CONSTRUCTION

1527
02:05:32,770 --> 02:05:35,440
"DEAR IZUMI, I'M IN TOWN ON BUSINESS.
YOU WERE OUT WHEN I CALLED."

1528
02:05:35,570 --> 02:05:37,480
"SO I HOPE TO SEE YOU
NEXT TIME I'M IN TOKYO."

1529
02:07:42,110 --> 02:07:47,530
<i>Goodbye isn't forever.</i>

1530
02:07:49,370 --> 02:07:54,450
<i>It's just until we meet again someday.</i>

1531
02:07:56,420 --> 02:08:03,210
<i>Even if I leave what I yearn for
behind in my dreams.</i>

1532
02:08:03,710 --> 02:08:10,350
<i>And my heart grows cold.</i>

1533
02:08:10,470 --> 02:08:17,310
<i>All I want right now.</i>

1534
02:08:18,270 --> 02:08:23,610
<i>Is to keep holding you forever.</i>

1535
02:08:24,530 --> 02:08:31,530
<i>I just want to stay like this.</i>

1536
02:08:32,950 --> 02:08:39,080
<i>And warm your cold cheeks against mine.</i>

1537
02:08:44,130 --> 02:08:49,340
<i>Everyone in the city
is always in such a rush.</i>

1538
02:08:51,430 --> 02:08:56,680
<i>And Love is trapped in a concrete cage.</i>

1539
02:08:58,480 --> 02:09:05,610
<i>But should you get tired
of those casual encounters.</i>

1540
02:09:05,730 --> 02:09:12,410
<i>Then be sure to come back to me.</i>

1541
02:09:12,530 --> 02:09:19,160
<i>The faces of the men I've loved.</i>

1542
02:09:20,330 --> 02:09:25,170
<i>Turn to mere memories.</i>

1543
02:09:50,530 --> 02:09:54,370
<i>My first ever kiss</i>

1544
02:09:56,490 --> 02:09:58,870
<i>was to a middle-aged man.</i>

1545
02:10:03,000 --> 02:10:04,250
<i>It Looks Like.</i>

1546
02:10:06,800 --> 02:10:09,170
<i>I'm going to grow up
to be a stupid woman.</i>

1547
02:10:10,510 --> 02:10:11,550
<i>The end.</i>

1548
